title: pink delight
directions: Place pineapple in a large saucepan.
Add jello and heat until jello dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into mold or bowl.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare gelatin per box directions, using 3 1/2 cups water. Combine cranberry sauce, pineapple and walnuts; add to gelatin. Congeal in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar in a bowl.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Serve.

title: frozen roll coffeecake
directions: The night before, place frozen rolls in a Bundt or tube pan sprayed lightly with Pam.
Melt 1 stick butter or margarine and pour over rolls.
Mix together all dry ingredients and pecans. Spread over rolls and butter.
Cover with towel and let set overnight (not in refrigerator).

title: lazy day stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Place in bottom of casserole dish. Pour frozen vegetables over beef.
Spread soup over top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for about 3 hours.

title: green beans and onions
directions: Boil green beans for about 10 minutes. Add ingredients and then cook for 10 more minutes on medium temperature.

title: sweet potato banana custards
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and bananas.
Add milk and mix well. Add brown sugar, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Spray 8 (1/2 cup) custard cups.
Arrange cups on baking sheet.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of mixture in each cup.
Bake in 325° oven for about 35 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: sunny banana pie
directions: Crust:
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Blend well and press into 9-inch pie shell.
Or microwave in a glass plate on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Rotate dish each minute.
Crust may also just be chilled.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Butter bottom only of glass baking dish.
Butter tops of bread and place in glass baking dish with buttered sides up.
Sprinkle drained sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat the eggs together with half and half. Pour over cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in sweetened condensed milk, then thawed whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, slice bananas into pudding mixture and layer with vanilla wafers into dessert dishes or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Keep chilled.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cold banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add sour cream; mix until smooth.
Line bottom and sides of dish with vanilla wafers.
Add a layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding.
Repeat.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crumble a few vanilla wafers on Cool Whip.
Refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion until hamburger is browned and onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly; lower heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: grilled orange roughy with tomato basil sauce
directions: For Grilling the Fish (for 4 people):
Brush fish with oil and lemon.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, dried basil and oregano over fish. Place fish on lightly oiled rack.
Grill over coals, 4 to 5 minutes per side, until done.
Remove fish.
Garnish with Tomato Basil Sauce and serve.

title: mom's salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together with milk and bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: grandmother's graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add baking powder, milk and crackers alternately. Add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Can be cooked in tube pan or 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cool.
Very rich.
If desired, can be served with the following filling, between the 3 layers.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: Make white sauce with flour, margarine and milk.
After thickened, add bouillon and veggies.
Simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Also good with clams.

title: onion patties
directions: Drop by tablespoon in deep hot fat.
Fry to a golden brown on both sides.
Flatten patties slightly when you turn them.

title: amish country stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Peel and cut the potatoes into pieces a bit larger than the meat. Clean the carrots, celery and onions and cut all into 1-inch pieces.
In a large baking pan/dish, or ceramic slow cooker pot, combine all the ingredients, except for the parsley.
Bake, covered, for 5 hours, without stirring.
Add parsley just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar; continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add uncooked rice, beef broth and onion soup.
Cook at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain.
Mix other ingredients together.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg, salt, flour and baking soda.
Add mashed bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: no roll pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt together into a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Mix salad oil and milk.
Pour over flour.
Blend with a fork.
Using clean fingers, press dough to line bottom and sides of pan.

title: sausage rounds
directions: Take dough from package and pinch together along separation line.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Divide each dough section in half. Place a sausage link on each.
Roll up and slice.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway comes out clean.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Fill well-greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and heat about 45 minutes in a 400° oven, then lay onions on and heat 5 minutes more.
Watch so onions don't burn.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: petits fours(for receptions and teas)
directions: Cream butter in mixing bowl.
Add sugar gradually; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spread evenly in buttered and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done; cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; finish cooling on wire rack. Cover with towel.
Cut into diamond shapes when ready to frost.

title: meringue kisses or "forgotten cookies"
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With electric mixer on high speed, beat egg whites until they stand up with stiff peaks.
Slowly, gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts and morsels.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and place in hot oven.
Turn off oven. Leave cookies in oven overnight or "forget" about them for at least 8 hours.

title: etouffee
directions: Saute onions in butter until real soft.
Add shrimp and cook about 10 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom and tomato paste.
Cook about 15 minutes longer on slow heat.
Serve over rice.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store in tightly covered jar in a cool, dry place.

title: carol's brownies
directions: Beat together oleo, sugar and eggs. Add vanilla, then flour mixture. Stir until smooth. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan slowly at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Trim fat from chops and use to brown meat (about 8 minutes per side).
In 3-quart shallow baking pan, place browned chops. Sprinkle rice around chops.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops and rice.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Microwave the first 4 ingredients on High 2 minutes.
After reaching hard boil, add the soda to the cooked syrup and stir. Put the popped corn in a large grocery bag.
Pour the syrup over the corn in the bag and fold down the end.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake bag well.
Turn bag over and microwave another 1 1/4 minutes. Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Break apart and enjoy!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Stir in carrots.
Bake in layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix the cocoa, flour, salt and 1 cup milk. Stir until smooth over low heat.
Mix egg yolks and the other cup of milk in small bowl. Beat until foamy.
Gradually pour in pan with cocoa mixture. Cook until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla. (Use egg whites to make meringue top.)
Put pie filling in cooked shell.

title: honey nut party mix
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil the oleo, honey and brown sugar.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet in preheated oven at 325° for 25 minutes. Stir once during baking.
Remove from oven and pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add raisins and coconut.
Mix well and place on 2 cookie sheets to dry; do not refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: chicken stuffed pineapple
directions: Cut the pineapple in half lenghtwise, including leaf area. With a sharp knife, cut around the inside perimeter, leaving a 1/2-inch shell.
Carefully remove the pineapple and cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.

title: citrus surprise
directions: Sweeten fruit with sugar.
Measure juice and add cold water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add measured liquid.
Chill 3/4 cup gelatin until slightly thickened (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Mix.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: bright punch
directions: Combine lemonade, orange juice and water.
Put sherbet and ice cream in bottom of punch bowl.
Break into small pieces.
Add juice and serve.
Yields 35 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Cook shrimp in margarine with Italian seasoning, garlic and green onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour, and mix well.
Remove shrimp only, then add a "small" amount of flour gradually until mixture thickens slightly, using low heat.
Add shrimp back into mixture.
Serve over linguine.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in small amount of oil until brown and drain well.
Add onions and spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.

title: lemon breeze
directions: Measure 1/4 cup sugar, margarine and cinnamon into small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to bubble, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add crumbs and mix well. Reserve 2 tablespoons for topping.
Press crumbs to the bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.

title: lime-orange catfish(servings: 6)
directions: Whisk together first 8 ingredients. Gradually whisk in olive oil until well blended. Remove half of juice mixture and set aside.

title: turkey manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti in boiling water about 18 minutes or until tender but still firm.
Drain well.
In a large skillet cook turkey until no longer pink.
Drain.
Stir in sauce; heat through.
Mix together egg, Ricotta, Mozzarella, parsley and Parmesan.
Stuff cheese mixture into shells.
Spoon 1/3 of the sauce mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place shells atop.
Top with remaining sauce mix; covering shells.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: candied yams and apples
directions: Combine apples and yams; pour into shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over entire casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes.
Baste yams and apples occasionally with the syrup in the casserole. Serves 6.

title: 4th of july-red, white and blue jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 pkg. raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add blueberry pie filling.
Pour into 13 1/2 x 9 1/4-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Cream the cream cheese, adding unflavored gelatin.
Heat half and half with 2/3 cup sugar.
Do not boil.
Remove and combine together with cream cheese mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour over first layer and refrigerate until set.
Dissolve 1 package raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Pour over second layer after it sets.
Refrigerate until set.

title: large chocolate chip cookie
directions: Combine ingredients and stir until moistened.
Place on a lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Kids love this.
It's quick and easy.

title: lasagna soup
directions: In a skillet, brown beef, onion, green pepper, celery and mushrooms until the beef is no longer pink.
Add garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper, tomatoes and tomato sauce (mixture should be thick).
Simmer.

title: steak au poivre (peppered steak) with garlic "butter"(heart healthy)
directions: Press 1 1/2 teaspoons crushed pepper into each steak with heel of hand.
In small bowl, combine lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce; set aside.
In another bowl, combine parsley, margarine and garlic.
Form into 2 equal balls and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Grease pie plate.
Spread 2 cups berries over the bottom. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and walnuts or pecans.
Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour and margarine.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apricot wine soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor. Chill until very cold. Serve garnished with a dollop of sour cream sprinkled with cinnamon. Serves 4.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together boiling water and jello and stir well.
Add sherbet and oranges.
Put in refrigerator until congealed.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in Sugar Twin until dissolved. Add peanut butter and syrup; blend well.
Add cream and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into freezer can and freeze until firm.
Makes one gallon.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix eggs with cottage cheese.
Put small amount of sauce into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Do not cook noodles.
Place layer of noodles.
Top with cottage cheese mixture, then top with cheese.
Repeat until all the ingredients are used, topping off with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, then bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven; let set for 5 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: hot chicken salad(casserole)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add chicken, celery, almonds, pepper, onion and pimento.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with diced bread.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften; grate Cheddar cheese.
Mince olives and onions.
Mix all ingredients leaving some pecans to roll balls in.
Makes 2 cheese ball.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours (except egg noodles).
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: lemon barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer sauce until thickened, about 4 minutes.
Let cool, then refrigerate.
(This will keep in refrigerator for about one week.)
Will make about 1-1/2 cups.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and spread in medium size baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Completely cool.

title: good potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all together. Put in 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan. Crush 2 cups cornflakes with 1/4 cup melted butter and put on top. Bake 45 minutes, covered, at 350°. Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, spices, salt and soda.
Mix together oil, raisins, nuts and pumpkin.
Combine the two mixtures, pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Combine butter or margarine, confectioners sugar and milk until desired spreading consistency.
Beat until creamy.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Mix sugars, egg, margarine and peanut butter in a large bowl. Stir in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Spread in a pan.
Bake until golden brown, 17 to 22 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare Peanut Butter Frosting; reserve 1/3 cup.
Stir cocoa and milk into remaining frosting until smooth.
If necessary, stir in additional milk until of spreading consistency.
Frost squares with cocoa frosting.
Drop Peanut Butter Frosting by teaspoonfuls onto cocoa frosting; swirl for marbled effect.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combine flour, baking soda and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies or 10 to 11 minutes for crisp.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sourdough rolls
directions: Sift the first 5 dry ingredients; stir in oil and buttermilk. Dissolve yeast in water; add to mixture.
Place in container with a sealed lid.
Store in refrigerator.
Roll desired amount in flour.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: orange pickled beets
directions: Boil above ingredients until syrup becomes quite thick. Remove cloves.
We used beet slices for this and with the small inside circle of a doughnut cutter (it slips out easily) we make tiny round circles of beets.
Let the beets stand for 48 hours in the syrup, then drain and serve.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Mix butter, oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, milk, cocoa, flour, baking soda, salt and zucchini.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss together and refrigerate to chill before serving.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare, core and cut up apples.
Arrange in pie crust.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with the flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or sharp Cheddar cheese.

title: cantaloupe sherbet
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over milk.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Place in blender container with cantaloupe and corn syrup; cover.
Blend on high speed 30 seconds.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover; freeze overnight.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, pork, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, ginger, nutmeg, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Blend together egg and milk.
Stir into meat mixture.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in single layer in shallow baking dish. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in preheated 325° oven.
Remove meatballs.
Measure 3 tablespoons drippings into skillet.
Blend in flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cook over low flame, stirring until flour mixture is smooth and bubbly. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Stir into flour mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add meatballs.
Simmer 35 to 40 minutes. Cool slightly.
Stir in sour cream and serve warm.
Makes about 5 dozen meatballs.

title: fruit bowl crunch
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine sugar and light syrup; stir constantly until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in flavored drink mix and salt until they dissolve. Immediately stir in popcorn; toss until evenly coated and gently toss with cereal.
Spread on greased cookie sheet until cool and hard.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Makes 11 cups of snack mix.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix 3 or 4 minutes until light. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 325° until top of cake springs back.
Cool cake upright in pan 15 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: May substitute 1 ounce can Ortega chilies and no pimento and no jalapenos.

title: chicken with zucchini
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Pour off fat and add soup and seasoning.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Add cut-up zucchini and cook 15 minutes more.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 1 1/2-inches).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn heat to 300° while cooking, about 25 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squashes and onion together for 5 minutes; drain.
Add soup, sour cream and carrots to drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix with melted margarine (do not add water, as package directs).
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of greased casserole.
Add squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers fine.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill until firm. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: pecan fingers pies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening and sugar together thoroughly.
Stir 1 1/2 cups flour into shortening mixture.
With hand, press and flatten mixture evenly in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake 20 minutes and cool.

title: 4-h barbecue cabbage salad
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and salt in bowl.
Add vinegar to make paste.
Add oil and vinegar in small quantities alternately.
Beat until thick.
Add celery seed. Pour over shredded cabbage. Refrigerate overnight.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together and coat biscuit pieces. Place into Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter around and over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cheese. Gradually add eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Butter spring-form pan. Coat with graham crackers. Gently pour in cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine 2 tablespoons oil, egg and buttermilk; stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each frankfurter into 5 pieces.
Dip each piece into batter, coating completely (use wooden picks to aid in dipping).
Pour oil to depth of 3 to 4 inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 375°.
Fry pieces until golden, turning once; drain on paper towels.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Flake crab meat.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until well browned.
Serves 6.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix all above ingredients except soup.
Form into meatballs. Roll in flour (lightly).
Place in lightly oiled baking pan. Bake at 350° until cooked.
Mix soup and water and pour over meatballs.

title: chicken pattie casserole
directions: Fry chicken patties until golden brown (not hard).
Boil broccoli or California Blend until soft.
Butter and season to your satisfaction.

Place chicken pattie in baking pan, cover each pattie with Swiss cheese (place patties next to each other). Drain broccoli and place on top of cheese (all the broccoli); add butter on top of broccoli (enough to season).
Mix the 3 eggs and mustard, 1/2 cup milk and stir well.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Mix tuna with mayo, pickle relish and onion.
Follow directions on box of puffs.
Spoon into puffs and top with cheese.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pan. Make cake batter. Pour half batter into pan. Bake 25 minutes. Heat caramels and milk in saucepan over medium heat. Pour caramel over warm cake in pan. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips. Spread remaining batter. Bake for 30 more minutes. Cool 1 hour before serving. Store at room temperature.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add eggs and fruit cocktail (and juice). Mix by hand. Pour into a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle over batter the brown sugar and nuts. Bake in 325° oven 40 minutes, then cool.

title: autumn surprise cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let stand until juice forms.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sun tea
directions: Place tea bags in water mixed with sugar and set in the sun for 1 day.
Chill and serve.

title: battletown inn squash
directions: Boil squash, then boil in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash squash, then drain again in sieve, pushing all liquid out.
Saute the onion in butter but don't brown.
Add crumbs, milk and drained squash.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour in greased casserole.
Top with dots of butter and fine bread crumbs.

title: cherry jubilee salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and cool to room temperature. Stir in pineapple, milk and pie filling.
Fold in topping and nuts.

title: best ever potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Add potatoes, broth, carrot, onion, parsley, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender (about 15 minutes).
Combine flour and milk until smooth and add to soup. Bring to a boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted and the soup is heated through.
Garnish with green onion, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large mixer bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Do not overmix.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: mother's lemon pie
directions: Boil milk.
Mix cornstarch and flour with sugar; then add 1/2 cup additional cold water and mix until smooth.
Beat egg yolks and add to flour mixture; then add to boiling milk, stirring all the while.
Place on stove and cook until it boils and becomes thick.
Add lemon juice and butter; pour into baked shell.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites and sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: frankfurters monterey
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, seasonings, juice of lemon and a thin strip of lemon rind.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove lemon rind.
Arrange franks over noodles in a large greased casserole dish and pour sauce over.
Bake uncovered in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes about six servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Boil 2 pints water, chili powder, cumin seed, garlic, catsup, salt and butter for 30 minutes.
Then add cornstarch and 1/2 cup water until thickens.
Keep warm.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix Bisquick, cinnamon and sugar and make a well in mixture. Drop in sour cream and egg.
Beat with a fork.
Add berries. Sprinkle tops with sugar and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: delicious punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in the water until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and ice cubes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In Dutch oven, combine onion, meat and garlic; cook until meat is browned and onion tender.
Skim off excess fat, remaining ingredients and 2 cups water.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw frozen bread (do not let rise).
Melt margarine, brown sugar, pudding and milk (do not cook).
Add walnuts, raisins and cinnamon.
Heat.
Break 1 loaf bread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, tearing off enough pieces to cover bottom.
Pour hot mixture over bread.
Break remaining bread over mixture.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn upside-down while hot.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Remove 1/2 and set aside. Stir tomato sauce, paste, water and brown sugar into sausage and simmer 15 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Drop by tablespoons into hot grease and fry on both sides until golden brown.

title: peach fluff pie
directions: Put jello, sugar and hot water (salt if desired) and add all juices, stirring to be sure everything is blended.
Let set to the consistency of thick unbeaten egg whites.
Add 1 cup of Cool Whip and peaches.
Put in ready-baked pie crust and serve with more Cool Whip topping.

title: linda's rice and nut vegetarian loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in oiled baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; immediately turn out onto a platter.
Garnish with carrot curls, parsley and tomato wedges.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mary ann's soup
directions: Add enough water to simmer until potatoes are done.

title: cake mix whoopie pies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread icing onto one patty and place a second patty on top to make a sandwich or whoopie pie.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix eggs, vinegar and sugar and cook until thick.
Pour over cream cheese, green pepper and onion.
Beat with mixer.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: soft cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: sticky buns
directions: Heat all ingredients, except bread dough.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, make walnut size balls from dough and lay in pan.
Do not layer.
Cover with sauce and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Turn onto a cookie sheet.

title: chili dip
directions: In a pie plate or similar shallow dish, spread the cream cheese, then the chili and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve warm as dip for corn chips or crackers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in pan; drain grease.
Stir spaghetti sauce into meat and onion.
Heat until it starts to boil.
Cook twists macaroni; place a layer in bottom of casserole (approximately 9 x 13-inch).
Cover with browned hamburger meat and spaghetti sauce mixture.
Top with layer of pepperoni slices; cover fairly generously with Mozzarella cheese.
I make 2 layers of each.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until the cheese is browned.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foaming.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold in crackers.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Grease pie dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. When cool, make top.
To Cool Whip, fold in preserves.
Spread on top crust and sprinkle with coconut.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Blend in flour. Stir milk and cream in slowly and continue to stir until smooth and it comes to a slow boil.
Add a little cream sauce to beaten yolks.
Mix well.
Add yolks to cream sauce and cook 1 minute. Add seasoning, cheese and spinach.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Set casserole in pan of water and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar, Blend in well beaten egg, vanilla, diced apples, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda. Stir in walnuts. Put into 8 or 9-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Top with lemon sauce or sour cream frosting.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Warm shortening and sugar; add egg and flavor.
Stir in dry ingredients and beat together good.
Chill in fridge.
Roll very thin.
Cover heavy with sugar.
Bake at 400° on baking sheet for 6 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except apples, in a large pan.
Add in 8 cups of water; bring to boiling while stirring.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the fruit is tender and tapioca is cooked.
Stir occasionally.
Add apple slices; simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Remove cinnamon.
Serve, warm or cold, as a dessert or first course appetizer.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in sugar gradually.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread frosting between layers, over top and around sides.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: easy prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cake mix in 9 x 12-inch pan and spread it evenly.
Drain pineapple.
Dump pineapple on top of mix.
Dump cherry pie filling on top.
Smooth out.
Dump nuts and coconut on top. Smooth out. Cut butter into pats and place on top.
"Good Eating!"
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: louisiana sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put mixture into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Cool before serving.

title: savory baked spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and dry meat.
Arrange spareribs meaty-side up in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 hour.
Combine cornstarch and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until boiling.
Remove from heat. Pour sauce over meat.
Bake 30 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream sugar, butter, buttermilk and vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
Mix together, then fold eggs in.
Mix.
Pour in 2 layer pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamsicle fudge
directions: Prepare 11 x 7 pan or what you have with 1 1/2 tsp. of the margarine. In heavy saucepan combine sugar, cream and remaining margarine. Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 4 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in the chips and marshmallow creme until smooth. Remove 1 cup and set aside. Add orange extract and food coloring to remaining, stir until well blended. Pour into pan. Drop the reserved by teaspoonful and cut through mixture with a knife. Refrigerate until set.

title: weight watchers chicken breast florentine
directions: Spray 10-inch skillet with nonstick cooking spray and heat. Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring constantly, until soft. Remove from heat; stir in spinach, cheese, 1/4 teaspoon salt, oregano and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Spread 1/4 of spinach over each breast, leaving 1/2-inch border on all sides.
Carefully roll chicken breasts crosswise to enclose filling and secure with picks.

title: corn muffin casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss pork chops in tomato sauce
directions: Heat 1 deep frypan or electric skillet.
Place oil in pan. Mix flour and spices together.
Cover chops in flour mixture. Place in hot oiled pan.
Fry brown on both sides under medium heat. Place sliced onions and green peppers over chops.
Pour tomato sauce mixture over chops.
Bring to boil, lower heat to simmer. Every so often, move chops around so they don't burn.
Serve with egg noodles-rice.
Use sauce as topping.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Stir in uncooked rice and salt.
Place chicken, skin side up.
Add water and onion soup.
Cover with foil and bake.
Cook at 400° for 1 hour.
When done, cover with grated cheese and brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: beverly's meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place mixture into glass dish. Microwave, uncovered, 20 minutes at full power.
Check center to cook thoroughly. Or use muffin pan cups or Bundt cake pan or put glass cup in center of mixture. Sides will look brown. Serve as an entree or sandwich filling.
Moist and wonderful!

title: pepperoni pasta pie
directions: Beat eggs with Parmesan and pepper.
Toss with cooked and drained macaroni.
Coat 2 (10-inch) pie plates with Pam spray. Divide ingredients, pat macaroni mixture in bottom of plate.

title: graham squares
directions: Partially melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in 9-inch pan (well-greased).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Combine the first 6 ingredients; beat 2 to 3 minutes with hand mixer.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Spread the remainder in a 9 x 13-inch pan, which is sprayed with Baker's Joy or Pam.
Spread the preserves over the dough; crumble the reserved portion over the preserves.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Boil chicken in water until it falls apart.
Remove and cool. Then
pick	the
meat
off and put back in broth.
Peel potatoes and
dice,	add
to broth.	Add the cans of corn and diced hard-boiled
eggs.	Let simmer until potatoes are soft. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: banana cake - low-fat
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside. Blend egg substitute, sugar, bananas and vanilla with blender. Add flour mixture; begin to blend, adding small amounts of buttermilk at a time until completely blended.
A 6 ounce package of chopped nuts may be added and blended in before pouring in your pan.
Use a Bundt or tube pan.
Take a piece of wax paper; trace the bottom of the pan, then cut with scissors and place cut piece of wax paper inside bottom of pan before pouring in batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: potato surprise
directions: Layer the following in a 9 x 13-inch dish, hash browns, onion to taste and salt.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, sour cream and milk.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese. Top with mixture of melted butter and cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmonettes
directions: Drain oil or water into a measuring cup off of salmon or tuna. Dump salmon into a mixing bowl and add the egg; mix well.
Add flour.
Mixture will be very thick.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Oleo and cream cheese should be at room temperature at least 2 hours.
Melt oleo in saucepan and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Place 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of pan.
Put both cans of pie filling on top of crumbs.
Prepare Cool Whip according to directions, then add sugar and whip.
Add cream cheese and whip. Spread over cherry pie filling.
Put rest of crumb mixture on top. Chill.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Turn into shallow buttered 2-quart casserole.
Combine cheese and potato chips and spread on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together Wesson oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one. Add cocoa, vanilla and red food coloring. Mix well, but do not overmix!

Sift flour and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk, ending with flour. Combine soda and vinegar and pour in cake mix while bubbling if possible. Mix together and pour in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Turn out on wire racks to finish cooling. Mix Icing ingredients together and spread on cooled cake.

title: carrie lewis' cake frosting
directions: Cream the milk and shortening.
Add sugar and cocoa, beating until smooth.
Add both flavorings and beat again.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Peel and sliced apples thin. Roll up apple slices in crescent rolls in strips. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Pour water, sugar and melted butter over apple slices wrapped in roll strips. Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let set for 15 minutes. Water and sugar mixture will thicken.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix soda, cinnamon, salt and flour together.
Add to oleo mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, mix well.
Add oatmeal, pecans, and raisins. Mix well.
Mixture will be stiff. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: 7-layer ribbon salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix one box cherry jello with 3/4 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Let each layer set before adding next layer.

title: chicken in sherry cream sauce
directions: Remove green peas and onions from pouch and partially thaw. Heat oil in wok.
Add mushrooms and stir-fry over medium heat about 3 minutes.
Add chicken pieces and continue stir-frying until chicken is white and firm.
Add partially thawed peas and onions, broth and sherry.
Cook over low heat.
Stir and break up block of vegetables as they cook.

title: cheese and asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus and eggs.
Mix the soup, butter and milk.
Pour over each layer of eggs and asparagus.
Put cracker crumbs and cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl; stir well.
Pour into greased preheated 8x8-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes to one hour at 375°; do not overbake.

title: beefsteak na kyselo(steak with sour cream gravy)
directions: Trim meat slices.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat shortening in heavy skillet.
When smoking hot, saute meat in it until browned on both sides.
Lower heat.
Sprinkle salt over meat and top with onion slices.
Pour water over meat.
Simmer, covered, for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Check liquid; at the end of cooking time, there should be about 1 cup of it. Remove meat to hot dish.
Blend sour cream with flour.
Stir into skillet and mix thoroughly with pan juices.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and add ketchup, if desired.
Heat through and pour sauce over meat.
Serve very hot with boiled noodles or boiled potatoes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and drain until dry.
(Use strainer and press spinach with a spoon, then drying in a paper towel.)
Slice chestnuts.
Combine all ingredients well.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350° or until it bubbles. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fresh pineapple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt into the eggs.
Add lemon juice and pineapple.
Pour in pastry-lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: chicken livers in mushrooms
directions: Clean livers in cool water and drain well. Saute in butter until tender and half done (10 or 15 minutes).
Add clean, washed mushrooms and cook until done (5 or 10 minutes). Add black pepper and a dash of Bouquet.
Makes a great gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: grandma cookies(10 dozen)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed ingredients. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes or until tops begin to brown.
Do not overbake or cookies will be dry.
Makes 10 dozen good cookies

title: basic roll dough
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir well.
Dough may be sticky.
Cover and raise until double in bulk.
Makes 2 loaves of bread or 1 loaf and 12 rolls.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: southern butter mints
directions: Cook sugar, butter and water together until when tested in water it builds a brittle "castle" in cup.
Pour on buttered marble slab immediately to remove heat quickly.
As soon as possible start pulling candy; add flavoring and coloring at this time.
Pull until white; then pull out in long strand and cut with scissors.

title: tuna bun-steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Split buns and fill with mixture.
Wrap individually in aluminum foil.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix spaghetti, Italian dressing, chopped vegetables and Salad Supreme.
Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: wiener and vegetable casserole
directions: Arrange vegetables and wieners in alternate layers in well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with a little salt, pepper, flour and margarine.
Top layer should be wieners; pour milk over all.

title: grandma perry's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and mix well in mixer at medium speed 2 to 3 minutes.
Slow mixer speed and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop onto cookie sheet about the size of a walnut for each cookie.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Monitor first batch to test your own oven.
Yields about 80 cookies.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix together the butter, stuffing mix and salt.
Cook vegetables slightly and drain.
Mix together soup, mayo, eggs and onion and add to vegetables.
Grease a deep casserole dish and add vegetables to it.
Mix most of the cheese into vegetable mixture and some of the stuffing mixture.
Put remaining cheese on top and remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage well.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard together.
Tear bread into small pieces.
Add bread, cheese and sausage to milk and egg mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool.
Add whole bottle of dressing. Mix and refrigerate overnight, then add green pepper, celery, tomatoes and cucumbers.
Add 1/2 jar McCormick Salad Supreme.
Mix well.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in small amount of water until tender; drain. In greased 2-quart casserole, sprinkle 1 tablespoon bread crumbs over bottom.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, flour and onion. Place layer of potatoes in casserole.
Salt to taste.
Add layer of egg slices.
Spread 1/2 creamy mixture over eggs.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons bread crumbs on top.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Options:
Cherry tomatoes (cut in half), shrimp, avocados, mushrooms, etc.

title: rigatoni ii
directions: In a large skillet, lightly brown ground beef. Add onion. On medium heat, stir in sauce and pepper. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. In a bowl, stir cottage cheese, milk and salt. Add rigatoni after cooking it about 10 minutes. Stir good. Spoon 1/2 of rigatoni on bottom of pan; top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients, shape and top with chopped nuts and cheese.
Chill until firm.
Decorate as desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: almond joy candy for dipping
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; boil to soft ball stage.
Cool, then add extract and coconut.
Shape into balls; refrigerate overnight before dipping.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in top of double boiler.
Add pecans. Drop 1 1/2 to 2-inch mounds on buttered pan.
Cool in refrigerator for at least 3 hours.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip candy mounds in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.
May be frozen.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Mix together and boil 5 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.
Return to fire and stir 2 minutes, add 1 bottle Certo.
Cook and stir 4 minutes.
Place in glasses with tops.
You may add 1 or 2 drops of green coloring, if desired.
Use big pan and wear rubber gloves.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together and put over rhubarb.
Let stand while making crust.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over rhubarb and mix.
Pour into a 9 or 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then turn oven back to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine the eggs, sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla in a bowl and beat with mixer at medium speed until thoroughly blended.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt and mix until smooth.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan and sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: two crust lemon pie
directions: Beat lemon, sugar and eggs together for 10 minutes.
Rub the butter and cornstarch (this probably means "cream the butter and cornstarch").
Mix thoroughly with the other ingredients.
Add the milk (water can be substituted if milk is not convenient).
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into a deep pie pan lined with crust and cover with a top crust.
Wet the edges of the pie crust and press tightly together.
Bake quickly (450°) until set.

title: sweet and sour yams and pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine juice from pineapple, cornstarch and salt in saucepan; mix well.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens, stirring.
Stir in vinegar.
Add yams and pineapple slices; cover and simmer.
Stir-fry onions, celery and green pepper in oil for 4 minutes.
Combine with yams and pineapple.
Serve immediately.

title: 20 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in big mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and unbeaten egg.
Add flour gradually, mixing well.
Beat, adding oil.
Fill greased muffin pan 1/3 full.
Let rise in warm place until double in size or at top of muffin tin.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375° for 30 minutes or at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: heavenly onions
directions: Simmer onions in oleo until tender.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and pepper.
Heat soup, milk and soy sauce, stirring until blended.
Pour over onions.
Stir gently. Overlay bread slices on top around edge of casserole.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then push bread slices down into onion mixture. Bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in Pyrex dish.
Layer a dish with vanilla wafers.
Put pudding on the wafers.
Cover with lite Cool Whip.
Add nuts (optional).

title: chutney
directions: Mix veggies with salt and let stand overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring until thick and clear.
Makes 3 pints.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool. Pour into baked 8-inch pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff and spoon onto top of pie. Return to oven and brown at 350°.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, egg yolks and 2 tablespoons of the milk until
light and fluffy.
Add 2 cups flour and remaining milk, alternating.
Add
soda
and
salt	to
the last 1/2 cup flour and carefully	blend into cake mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites
and
vanilla.
Last, stir in nuts.	Bake in oblong pan or in 2 (9-inch) layer pans for 35 to 40 minutes in 325° oven.
Frost with Seafoam Frosting.

title: messetti
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Cook pepper, onion and celery until tender.
Cook
noodles
by	package
directions.
Combine
all ingredients
together except cheese.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Bake
at 350° for 1	hour and 5 minutes before ready to sprinkle with cheese.

title: frank fiesta one dish dinner
directions: Cook
franks and onion in oil (use skillet) until onion is tender.
Add other ingredients, except green pepper.
Bring to boil,
cover and simmer until macaroni is tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Add green pepper and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual.
Thaw broccoli in boiling water.
Drain. Mix all ingredients, adding broccoli last.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Place apple slices in large bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon, 5 tbsp. of sugar and oil, orange juice, and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with eggs and remaining sugar. Grease 10 inch tube pan and dust with flour.
Pour 1/3 batter into pan.
Layer with apples and repeat until you end with apples on top.
Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours or until golden on top.
Let cool a few minutes, then unmold on to a plate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and peanut butter, then beat in the confectioners sugar.
Stir in 4 ounces (1/2 tub) of the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and put in freezer for 15 minutes to set.
Remove from freezer and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top in pretty pattern and top with nuts.

title: coconut cake delight
directions: Mix cake ingredients and bake as recommended on box.
Can omit oil as instructed on box for "light" recipe.
If you do not use oil, add 1/3 extra water.

title: individual apple crisps
directions: Place the cinnamon and apple pieces in a resealable plastic bag.
Toss to coat the apple pieces.
Put the coated apple pieces in a microwave-safe dish.
Cook in the microwave until the apples are softened.
Remove the apple pieces from the microwave and stir in the granola and raisins.
Top with ice cream.

title: spiced coffee mix
directions: Mix and blend well all ingredients.
Use 2 teaspoons mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients until well blended.
Serve with assorted fruit.

title: heavenly banana pudding
directions: Take one pudding mix and mix as directed on box.
Take the other package and mix with Eagle Brand milk, then fold them together with the Cool Whip.
Layer wafers and bananas with the pudding.

title: bavarian cream
directions: Blend thoroughly the sugar, gelatin, milk and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil (do not boil).
Place pan in cold water immediately. Cool until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon. Fold in 1 cup whipped cream, whipped, or 2 cups Cool Whip and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into buttered 1-quart mold or individual buttered molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on large serving dish. Garnish with sweetened whipping cream and fresh fruit (strawberries, raspberries or peaches!).

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix sour cream, eggs and sugar.
Add cream cheese and vanilla. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Saute chopped onion and green onions in margarine until clear. Add soup and cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted. Add broccoli and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add Tabasco and salt to taste.
Serve with Melba toast or crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Let cool.
Crumble 1 layer of cake in bottom of a punch bowl.
Prepare instant pudding, use 1/2 of pudding on first cake layer.
Slice bananas, put 1/2 over pudding.
Pour 1/2 can pineapple (with juice) over bananas.
Put strawberries 1/4-inch deep over bananas.
Top with 1 carton Cool Whip.
Repeat the process, ending with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and refrigerate.

title: fried corn
directions: Put corn into skillet and cover with milk.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring mixture to boil and boil until almost dry.
Stir often.

title: jello salad
directions: Be careful in your selections; do not choose too young and take only such varieties as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere.
When once decided upon and selected, let that part remain forever settled and give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.

Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others are constantly getting them into hot water. Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste; then wrap well in a mantle of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: easy mix pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix for 10 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Day before:
Boil ham hock and Portuguese sausage until ham hock is tender enough to be shredded.
Skim fat; discard skin/bones.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: candy covered dried fruit
directions: Dip half of each piece of the dried fruit into melted chocolate and place on wax paper to dry.

title: ice cream
directions: To well beaten eggs, beat in 2 cups sugar and dash of salt. Dissolve the gelatine in 1/2 cup water.
Scald the 2 cups milk. Add gelatine. Beat into egg mixture along with syrup, Milnot and vanilla.
Put into container and add milk to fill container.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice and layer cooked potatoes in baking dish.
Cover with next 4 ingredients which have been mixed together.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Place in bottom of tube pan. Spread ice cream over cake.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water, add strawberries and stir until strawberries are unfrozen. Pour over ice cream and freeze.

title: southern fried chicken with creamy gravy
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix dry ingredients.
Heat oil (1/4-inch) in large skillet.
Coat chicken with flour mixture. Cook in oil over medium heat, 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until thickest pieces are tender.
Turn chicken to assure even cooking.
Remove cover for last 5 minutes to crisp chicken.
Place chicken on platter.
Pour fat from pan into bowl leaving brown particles in pan.
Return 3 tablespoons fat to pan.
Blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in 3/4 cup milk and 3/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Let boil 1 minute.
Add few drops bottled Brown Bouquet sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each.
Add vanilla and black walnut flavoring.
Sift all dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to cream mixture. Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 80 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting (optional).

title: chicken and potato dumplings
directions: Place chicken, celery, parsley, salt and pepper into a large pan; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 or 3 hours until the chicken is tender; drain the chicken, keeping the broth. Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Return meat to the broth. Mix together remaining ingredients, adding enough chicken broth to make a thick dough.
Bring broth to a boil and drop dumpling mix by spoonfuls into broth.
Cook over low heat for about 15 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Beat sugar, butter, margarine and eggs until fluffy.
Add lemon juice and flour.
Mix well.
Pour in ungreased cookie sheet and spread with cherries on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: crabmeat mold
directions: Mix celery, onion, crab and undiluted soup.
Cut up cream cheese in pan; melt until smooth.
Add to mixture.
Mix 1/4 cup warm water with gelatin.
Mix well and add.
Stir in 1 cup mayo; mix well.
Grease Jell-O mold with Pam.
Chill until firm, 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with crackers or raw veggies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool and skin; cut into cubes.
Cut bread, onions, green pepper and cheese into cubes.
Combine in large bowl.
Pour melted margarine over.
Add pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Place in casserole and bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple turnover pastries
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Roll pie crust into a 10-inch square on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into sixteen,2 1/2-inch squares.
Combine apples, brown sugar, cinnamon and egg in a large bowl and toss to mix.
Place pastry squares on an ungreased baking sheet.
Spoon 1 tablespoon apple mixture onto each square, dot with 1/4 teaspoon butter.
Fold each pastry over filling to form a triangle:brush pastry with some milk and press to seal.
Bake until golden brown (about 10 minutes).
Makes 16 turnovers.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring; add to Crisco mixture.
Mix salt and vanilla with buttermilk; add alternately with flour.
Beat well with an electric mixer.
Mix soda and vinegar; fold in.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together all ingredients and sift.
Store in jars.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Stir well and let stand together 8 hours.

title: creamed eggs
directions: In a heavy saucepan melt butter.
Stir in flour, dry mustard, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Carefully stir in eggs.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over toasted bread or English muffins.

title: eufala's red hot apples
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook the water, sugar and red drops until all the sugar and red drops are dissolved into syrup.
Peel and core apples.
Place 5 or 6 apples into the syrup and cook. Turn over one at a time when the top side becomes red. Cook until you can stick a fork into them.
When the apple is red and tender, lift out individually and put on a dish.
Continue with the remaining apples. Cook the syrup until near jelled. Fill each center. Freezes well.

title: lite delight jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple into a cup and add enough water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add to Jell-O. While Jell-O is hot, mash cream cheese into it; then add pineapple and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, mix soup, milk, & pepper.
Stir in beans and 2/3 cup french fried onions.
Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
Stir; top with 2/3 cup french fried onions.
Bake for 5 more minutes until onions are golden.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown, about 40 minutes.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, and stir in the flour and salt. Divide the dough in half.
Color 1/2 red, 1 tsp each color.
Roll into 4 inch strip, place strip side by side press lightly and twist into rope and make a cane.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 9 minutes in 375° oven, while still warm sprinkle with 1/2
cup crushed peppermint candy and 1/2 cup sugar. (Makes 4 dozen cookies).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place washed and sliced potatoes into buttered casserole, 9 x 13-inch.
Pour milk over top.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in the warm water.
Pour hot milk over sugar, shortening and salt in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Blend in 1 cup flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in yeast.
Add about 1/2 remaining flour and beat until very smooth.
Beat in the eggs. Beat in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as instructed on box in sheet cake pan.
Bring sugar, milk and 1 package of frozen coconut to a boil.
While cake is still hot, pour mixture over cake and cover to hold moisture in.
Let cool.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining package of frozen coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix thoroughly first 4 ingredients.
Sift the remaining ingredients and stir into first mixture.
Roll into balls the size of large walnuts and roll tops in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Yield: approximately 4 dozen.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cube pork shoulder butt and place in large pot with about 2 quarts water.
Place onion, celery, carrot and potato in blender with a little water.
Blend and pour in pot with pork.
Rinse split peas and add to pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for about 3 to 4 hours.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each one.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Sift flour and salt three times before measuring; add to mixture.
Add flavorings in small amounts at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan lined with wax paper.

title: bars of brickle
directions: Cream the butter with the sugar and corn syrup.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Stir in the brickle bits and press the mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Cook sausage until done; drain.
Saute vegetables.
Combine sausage, vegetables and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade thousand island dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise with the ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini
directions: Boil zucchini in water for 5 minutes or less.
Do not overcook.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over zucchini.
Mix well.
Marinate overnight.
Serve with pimento stuffed olives and slices of avocado.

title: apricot sauced duck
directions: Peel orange, reserving peel, break into quarters and set aside. Scrape the white membrane from peel and cut remaining peel portion into thin strips. Lightly salt cavity of duck. Stuff loosely with onion, apples and quartered orange. Tie legs of duck to tail. Prick legs and wings with fork to allow fat to escape. Place duck in shallow roasting pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and top with corn flakes, mixed with melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat; drain off grease.
Add other ingredients; cook about 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: wassail
directions: In large pan heat cider and cinnamon stick to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve in punch bowl and float Orange Stars.

title: strawberry rhubarb crisp(yield: serves 8)
directions: 1. Soak rhubarb in 1/2 cup of sugar for 1 hour cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut strawberries in quarters.

title: banana egg nog
directions: Add banana and egg to milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill and pour in container.
Shake before using.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in a 3 quart rectangular casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(Bake covered for 30 minutes.
Uncover, stir and finish baking uncovered.)
Sprinkle paprika on top for color.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, 2/3 cup margarine and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add brown sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and salt.
Mix just enough to blend.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and mashed bananas.
Beat in egg; add sifted flour and baking soda.
Melt butter or oleo in pan; tilt pan to butter sides.
Pour excess in batter.
Add nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix in separate dish the soup and sour cream.
Wrap meat in bread wraps.
Pour soup and sour cream mixture over top of enchiladas.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until hot (about 10 to 15 minutes) or until cheese is melted.
Top with lettuce, salsa, onions and olives.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium size pot.
Add salt and macaroni bring back to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat to a gentle boil.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and add sauce.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra in hot jars; put garlic bud in each jar.
Pour boiling brine in jars and seal.
Process in boiling water at simmering temperature for 10 minutes.
Let set several weeks before opening.
Yields 4 to 5 pints.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Place sliced potatoes in dish; pour over soup mix.
Then top with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: savory grilled potatoes in foil
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onions to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among 6 (12-inch) square pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Seal each to form packet.
Place foil packets on grill over medium-hot coals.
Grill, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Grilling time: 30 minutes.

title: arizona broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salad dressing and chopped onions.
Pour over broccoli and raisins.
Cook bacon very crispy; crush and sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put all ingredients (except sour cream) into bowl.
Stir in 1 container sour cream.
If mixture looks dry, add more sour cream until it is the texture you prefer.
This recipe can be made one day ahead.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and drizzle oleo over the top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
This makes a big amount.

title: fresh peach muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix milk, oleo and egg; add to dry mixture.
Stir only to moisten.
Do not beat!!
Fold in peaches including juice.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: alfredo with pasta
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add cream, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until thick. At the same time, bring water to boil and add your pasta.
When alfredo sauce has reached desired consistency stir in Parmesan cheese.
When pasta is cooked, serve or pasta plates with alfredo poured over the top.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in large pan over low heat, crumbling meat with a fork.
Drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat with chili powder, salt and sugar; mix well.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, water and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf.
Add beans to pot.
Thicken with a few instant potatoes. Cover and simmer another 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain about 50 cherries.
Pat dry on paper towels; set aside. Combine butter, syrup and salt, stirring well.
Stir in powdered sugar and knead in bowl until smooth.
Shape 1/2 teaspoon mixture around each cherry.
Place on waxed paper lined baking sheet. Chill about 2 hours or until firm.
Combine chocolate and shortening in top of a double boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate melts.
Dip each cherry by the stem into the chocolate.
Place on a waxed paper lined baking sheet.
Chill until firm.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.
Yields about 50 cherries.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend in blender:
Cream cheese, egg, vinegar, sugar, salad oil, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Chill about 1/2 hour, until very thick.
Pour over broccoli, raisins and onion. Fry bacon and crumble over broccoli mixture.

title: christmas punch
directions: Pour over frozen ice or cubes with cherries frozen in ice or cubes.

title: mona's congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Let cool and add pineapple.
Put in refrigerator and let stay until beginning to congeal, slightly around sides.
Take out; beat slightly.
Mix rest of ingredients together and return to refrigerator.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes by hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until inserted knife comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes its own crust.
Use 1 large or 2 small pie pans.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello and sugar with water until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients; blend well. Refrigerate until set completely.
Once well set, you may top with sliced pineapple.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Lightly brown the hash browns in 2 tablespoons of margarine. Mix the milk and soups in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add the hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix honey and mustard until mustard is dissolved. Serve hot or cold. Dip with chicken nuggets or use on your sandwich.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put the uncooked chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the ingredients together and put over the chicken.
Put into the oven at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sealtest sour cream chicken nachos
directions: Combine sour cream, process cheese and picante sauce in saucepan; stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Stir in chicken.

title: white grape spritzer
directions: Mix all ingredients into a punch bowl. Serves 24.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine; add seasonings.
Pour over all other ingredients and mix well.
Put in shallow pan and put in 200° oven for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir and mix while cooking.
Let cool and put into a tight container.

title: egg pie or custard
directions: Mix all ingredients well (use flavoring of your choice, such as nutmeg, ginger, allspice and cinnamon).
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Cook at 350° until firm.

title: lively lemon sauce
directions: In medium size heavy saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients until combined.
Cook over high heat, stirring frequently, until mixture comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Refrigerate until completely chilled before serving. Makes 2 cups.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil to hard ball stage. Remove from fire. Add soda.
Pour immediately over 4 quarts of dry popped corn.

title: showcase salad
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill about 3 hours.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients. Dip slices of bread into egg mixture until coated.
Melt 2 tsp. butter or margarine in pan and brown each side.

title: cindy's cookie mix
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Cut in shortening and store in a covered container up to 6 weeks at room temperature.
For longer storage, freeze.
To measure, spoon mix into measuring cup and level.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until barely tender (2 to 3 minutes). Drain well and cool.
Put remaining ingredients, except cheese, bread crumbs and butter, in blender. Blend well and add cooled squash.
Butter oblong glass baking dish generously and sprinkle bottom and sides with bread crumbs. Add cheese to squash mixture and pour into dish.
Sprinkle more bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Let sit for 10 minutes until mixture sets.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow. Put in greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet-sour beets
directions: Wash
and
trim
beets;
put
in
saucepan
with 1-inch boiling water; add salt to taste.
Bring to a boil;
cover and simmer for	25 to 45 minutes or until beets are tender.
Drain and reserve
cup	beet liquid; peel and slice beets; set aside. In	saucepan, mix reserved liquid, brown sugar, orange juice, lemon
juice
and cornstarch; bring to a boil, cooking until thickened.	Add
beets and heat, stirring until glazed; keep warm.
In
a skillet, saute pecans in butter; add beets, salt, pepper and parsley.

title: split pea soup(slow cooker)
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Remove ham bone.
Cut off meat; dice and return to pot.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: wesson oil brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and sugar; gradually add to first 3 ingredients.
Mix in oil; add melted chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into 7 x 11-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn out.
Frost if desired.

title: beef burgundy(vegetable medley)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Add bacon and cook until fat is rendered.
Remove bacon to heavy, flame-proof casserole.
Brown beef in skillet in small batches, sprinkling with pepper.
Remove to casserole with bacon.
In same skillet, quickly saute leeks, carrots and parsnips or turnips, sprinkling with sugar to caramelize slightly.
Remove from skillet and reserve.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Strain spices from mixture and discard.
Return cider to pan and keep warm until ready to serve.
(I use crock-pot to keep warm.)

title: peach cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter; add milk, almond extract, baking powder and flour.
Pour over peaches.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt; pour over batter.
Pour water over all.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: good meat loaf
directions: Mix together until all milk is absorbed completely into meat. Form into loaf.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Combine ingredients. Roll into balls and refrigerate.
Melt paraffin and bits in a double boiler. Remove from heat. Dip balls in chocolate to coat. Place on waxed paper.
Makes 60 to 70 balls.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: pasta goulash
directions: Boil pasta and drain.
Cook hamburger with chopped onions and bell pepper until hamburger is brown.
Add all other ingredients and cook 30 minutes longer.
Mix well.
Serves 6 people.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water; add sugar and salt.
Stir to dissolve.
Add egg, soft margarine and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue working dough, with hands, until smooth and elastic.
Brush top of dough with melted margarine.

title: orange punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water; cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients and serve chilled over ice.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients with beater.
With a wooden spoon mix in 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned beef roast
directions: Heat oil in the bottom of a heavy dutch oven or roaster with tight fitting lid that can go from burner to oven.
Dredge salted and peppered roast in flour, covering both sides.
Place roast in hot oil.
Brown well.
Add 3 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper to taste around roast in oil in bottom of pan.
Stir while cooking until flour is slightly brown.
Add water.
Stir to mix flour and water well.
Cover roaster with lid and place roast in a 450° oven. Cook about 30 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours depending on size of roast.
