title: wyoming zucchini bread("a favorite from the 76 cookbook.")
directions: Grease and lightly flour two 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
In mixing bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and shredded zucchini. Mix until blended.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: onion-cucumber salad
directions: Pull lines of fork firmly down length of the cucumber, repeating until thinly sliced.
Thinly slice onions, separating rings.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Marinate at least 1 hour.
Drain to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: e-z lemon pie
directions: Combine milk and lemonade.
Add Cool Whip and stir slowly. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until serving time. Garnish with graham cracker crumbs.

title: pineapple lemon cake
directions: Grease oblong pan.
Pour in 1 can crushed pineapple.
Pour 1 box Hinds lemon cake mix over the top.
Do not stir.
Then add oleo and butter (cut up).
Top with nuts.
Bake at 325° about 55 minutes.
Serve warm topped with whipped cream.

title: barney's cock-a-doodle-doo canape
directions: Combine cream cheese and a small amount of anchovy paste. Spread toasted rounds of bread with the cream cheese mixture. Place a slice of ham, tomato and egg over each.
Combine the remaining ingredients and a small amount of the tartar sauce mixture over each canape.
Arrange on a serving tray and serve at once.

title: creamy fruit dressing
directions: Blend cream cheese, lemon juice, and jelly.
Add whipped heavy cream and mix.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry-orange sauce(pancake topping)
directions: Puree 2 cups strawberries in blender.
Pour into small saucepan.
Add sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, just until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in remaining berries, orange juice, orange peel and vanilla.
Chill until ready to serve. Makes 2 cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss together ingredients except cheese and potato chips. Place mixture in sprayed loaf pan.
Top with cheese and chips. Bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients, except cracker meal, together. Pack mixture well into cleaned crab shells. Sprinkle with cracker meal. Place in baking pan and bake about 30 minutes. This is also a good stuffing for shrimp or fish. Yield: 8 deviled crabs.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Pat uncooked hamburger in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up either celery, onion, green pepper or whatever you prefer and put on top of hamburger.
Pour mushroom soup (undiluted) over this.
Then put a layer of Cheddar cheese (2 cups) and cover with Tater Tots. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(The recipe may also be divided in half.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add brown sugar and cinnamon. Stir in oil, pumpkin, eggs, water and nuts; mix well. Grease and flour 3 small pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Line pie pans with unbaked pastry.
Preheat oven at 450°. Combine pumpkin, sugar and remaining ingredients.
(If desire, use 2 teaspoons cinnamon, 3/4 teaspoon ginger and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg instead of pumpkin pie spice.)
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat quickly (leave oven door slightly open for 5 minutes) to 325°.
Continue baking for 30 minutes at 325° or unti knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tofu patties
directions: Saute celery and onion in small amount of water.
Mix tofu, bread crumbs and seasoning.
Add celery and onion.
If very dry, add just enough water to form patties easily.

title: rolled cookies(cutout)
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, egg and flavoring.
Sift flour and baking powder and add.
Chill dough.
Roll out thin.
Cut desired shapes. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese dip in a bread bowl
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a bowl to soften for about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, take the round bread and slice off the top. Hollow out.
Save top and inside of bread to place around the bowl for dipping.
When cheese is soft, slowly add the beer and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Pour into bread bowl and refrigerate. Serve on a round bread board or platter with reserved bread, crackers and party bread.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water in small dish.
Bring to boil pineapple juice and sugar, then add to gelatin and mix well.
Set mixture in refrigerator to settle and cool but do not allow mixture to harden.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow baking pan, skin side up. Combine butter, honey, mustard, salt and curry powder and mix. Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes, until chicken is tender and nicely browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper, corn and tomato soup and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix up cornbread and spoon over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cornbread is brown.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Rinse scallops and drain well.
Blend soup and flour. Gradually stir in milk and wine.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese and parsley.
Fold scallops into sauce and spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: yuletide egg nog
directions: After separating egg whites and egg yolks into separate large bowls, beat each until stiff peaks form.
Also in a separate bowl, beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Add 1 cup sugar to both yolks and whites and beat for approximately 5 minutes until sugar is dissolved.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans with fork and add all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until set and browned.
Let cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: meat salad
directions: Brown meat in oil; add lettuce.
Let it wilt.
Chop vegetables; add vegetables and rest of ingredients to meat.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onion together.
Add salt, pepper, butter and milk.
Mash all of them together.
Put in baking pan.
Cover with American cheese.
Put in oven until cheese has melted.

title: scramble(party mix)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large baking pan; bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix
the
flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add	apples;
stir
to barely cover.
In another bowl, mix eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.	Add nuts.
Bake
for
minutes at 350° in 2 greased loaf pans. (May also use tube pan, Bundt pan or a 13 x 9-inch pan.)

title: victorian rose scones
directions: Blend together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter.
Mix together whipping cream, egg and vanilla and add to mixture.
Roll out and cut into circles.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Serve with jam and whipped cream.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Add boiling water to raisins, sugar, shortening and baking soda in large bowl.
Let stand overnight.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 1 package of yellow cake mix according to directions on package.
Pour into prepared pan.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta, eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon flavor.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour over cake batter. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Freezes well.
Also on individual pieces you can sprinkle with rum just before serving.

title: buttermilk-toasted oat scones
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread oats and oat bran in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until light brown.
Cool.
Increase oven to 400°.

title: sourdough oat bread
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until foamy.
Add oil and sourdough starter.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
On a lightly floured board, knead lightly for about 2 minutes.
Place into greased pans; let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cover pans with foil; bake another 15 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped on bottom.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lots of macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix with pepper, onion and carrots. Combine milk, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over mixture and let sit overnight without stirring.
Mix well before serving.
Serves 16.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Crisco in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs in one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add to batter.
Mix in milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Drain and rinse peppers. Place on paper towel to dry.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: date nut bread
directions: Add boiling water to chopped dates and cook about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cream shortening.
Add honey gradually, beating well.
Add egg and beat.
Add date mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts. Mix well.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: holden family dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Combine milk and salad oil. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Drop from tablespoons on top of bubbling stew. Cover tightly and bring to a boil. Reduce heat (don't lift cover) and simmer for 15 minutes. Makes 5 servings.

title: sugar free punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before using or may serve over ice.
Makes 30 -35 servings.

title: reindeer fodder
directions: Melt almond bark and pour over all ingredients.
Stir well. Store in plastic containers.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham cracker crumbs and cinnamon.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Press on bottom and 1 1/2-inch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: baked garlic appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Remove papery outer skins from garlic. Slice top off bulbs so each clove is exposed.
Trim base so garlic can sit flat in base of baker.
Drizzle olive oil over bulbs.
Then top with pieces of butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano. Put chicken stock into base dish.
Cover with foil, making a dome lid.
Bake 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 275°.
Remove foil and bake another hour or until garlic is tender and husks are golden brown. Baste occasionally with olive oil, adding more stock to dish if necessary.
Serves 4 to 6. Serve with crusty hot French bread. Mash with fork and spread on bread with a dip of olive oil seasoned with Italian spices.
This recipe is loved by our family and friends.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bowl 1:
Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Bowl 2:
Beat sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Bowl 3:
Mix pineapple, yogurt, extracts and lime rind.
Add flour mixture and pineapple mixture to sugar mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Glace with lime juice and confectioners sugar, mixed to a good consistency.
Pour over top.
Let sit to dry.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients. Cook, until bubbling, on medium heat.
Stir often.
Pour into large pan, top with Doritos and sprinkle with cheese.
Place in oven around 400°.
Remove when cheese melts.

title: gelatin cherry pie
directions: Combine wafers, sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Press into 9-inch pie pan to form pie shell.
Set aside.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Beat eggs
and	sugar
well.
Add
sweetened
condensed milk, soda pop and 1 can condensed milk; mix well.
Pour into freezer can.
Add remaining cans of milk and vanilla.
Finish filling can with whole milk.
Freeze.

title: jadra (lentils and rice)
directions: In heavy
pot
fry onion in oil until golden brown or a little darker.
Set
aside.
In
another
pot
put lentils in enough water
to
cover.
Bring
to
a
boil and cook 20 to 30 minutes until almost done.
When almost done, add onion, rest of oil,
raw rice, salt and pepper.
Put enough water like you are cooking rice
plus the lentils, water to make 2 to 3 cups liquid.
Check about
minutes later and add more liquids. The dish should be firm.
Mix and serve.

title: baked fish
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces and put in greased baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and spread on fish (may do this before cutting up).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Fish will flake easily when done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and onion and form into ball.
Roll in almonds. Chill.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla and pineapple.
Add 1 cup pecans and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then remove and cool completely.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Wash cranberries. Heat oil to hot in saucepan. Add wet berries when oil is hot. Stir until berries pop their skin. Add sugar and cook over medium heat until syrupy. Add other ingredients and cook until it has good body. Spoon into jars like jelly. It keeps a season very well in refrigerator or process to seal.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Put apple butter between layers.

title: thomas jefferson's sweet potato biscuits(makes about 1 dozen biscuits.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a baking sheet and set aside. In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, spices and salt. Add the lard and cut in with a pastry cutter until the mixture is crumbly. Add the sweet potato and stir until well blended. Add the cream and pecans and stir until the dough is just moist. Transfer to a lightly floured work surface; roll out 1 1/2-inches thick and cut out rounds with a 2-inch biscuit cutter. Roll the scraps together and cut out more rounds. Arrange the rounds on the prepared baking sheet about 1-inch apart and bake in center of the oven until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes. Serve warm or let cool on a wire rack.

title: tandy take kake
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter and candy bar.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet or 13 x 9-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While still hot, spread on peanut butter and place in refrigerator to harden.
Melt chocolate candy bar in double boiler or microwave and spread on top of cake.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt butter in small frypan. Add coconut and cook until browned. Add brown sugar and Rice Krispies and blend. Spread 3/4 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream over Rice Krispies. Put remaining Rice Krispies mixture over ice cream. Put in freezer until ready to serve. Spread any pie filling over just before serving.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine chocolate chips and margarine. Stir well and heat over low heat until smooth and melted.
Add Eagle Brand; mix.
Spoon flour into measuring cups, level off.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla. Mix.
Shape 1 tablespoon dough around each candy kiss.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cookies become firm as they cool.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together remaining ingredients and mix into creamed ingredients.
Make balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or less.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with ketchup the last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: ever ready "spiced tea"
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoonfuls in a cup of boiling water, as you make tea.
Store in a tight sealing jar.
Will keep on the shelf for months.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill well.
Serve chilled with fresh, raw vegetables.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Butter your casserole dish lightly.
Mix together salsa and cooked beef.
Place tortilla in dish to cover bottom; spoon beef and salsa and sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle cheese on top layer of tortilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana variety bread
directions: Combine butter, honey, beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Then add liquid (this can be fruit juice of any kind, a soft drink or even beer).
Add vanilla and dry milk (substitute chocolate milk powder, hot cocoa mix, Tang or Kool-Aid, if desired).
Then add baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
If desired, fold in peanut M & M's or chopped nuts by hand.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This is a very versatile recipe; use your imagination to come up with new taste treats!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion in a little oil.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, broth and taco mix.
Heat this real good. Pour chips in baking dish and pour this mixture over them.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top. Place in a 400° oven and heat until mixture begins to bubble. Serve hot.

title: faye's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger over medium fire. Cook onion with meat. Drain. Add spaghetti seasons packet to drained meat. Add bell pepper, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Stir together, then add tomato sauce, puree and whole tomatoes.
Reduce fire and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Cook noodles 15 minutes before sauce is done.

title: tomato tart
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 10 inch tart pan with pastry dough.
Spread bottom of pastry with cheese and sprinkle with basil.
Cover with tomato slices, arranging to cover as evenly as possible.
Sprinkle tomatoes with salt and pepper and drizzle with olive oil.	Bake 30 to 40 minutes.	Slice in wedges and serve warm or at room temperature.

title: don ho chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large Ziploc bag.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Seal and marinate in refrigerator up to 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Grill over medium heat until chicken is cooked through.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Bake in muffin pan or iron skillet at 375° until golden brown.

title: endive and blue cheese salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Trim the endive and separate into leaves.
In a small jar, shake together the vinegar, salt and pepper until the salt dissolves.
Add the oil and shake again to combine.
Arrange the endive leaves on a serving plate with the Blue cheese and onion in the center.
Pour the dressing over all.
Toss and serve at the table.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crumble crackers in large dish.
Add eggs, pickles, olives, celery, tomatoes and pepper.
Mix together.
Add mayonnaise and stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add the beaten egg; mix until crumbly.
Put peaches into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon the flour and egg mixture onto the top of peaches. Pour the melted margarine over the top of flour mixture; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until slightly browned on top.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Place cooked broccoli in blender and add approximately 1/2 of the evaporated milk.
Blend well. Place the contents of the can of soup, diluted, into a saucepan. Add the broccoli and milk mixture; stir well.
Add the remaining milk and the grated cheese.
Simmer on medium-low heat until the cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix real well and let set a while.

title: pastry puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add flour.
Cool mixture before adding eggs, so they don't cook.
Stir in eggs separately. Cook on buttered tins at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown and crusty top.
Don't open oven door often, or puffs will fall. Stuff with pudding, salad, ice cream, etc.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12-cup muffin pan.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in applesauce.
Sift flour, baking powder and sugar together.
Stir into butter mixture until dry ingredients are moist.
Add nuts.
Fill each muffin cup 3/4 full. Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove upside down on wire rack to cool.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over very low heat.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in condensed milk, butter and vanilla.
Blend until butter is mixed with the chocolate.
Stir in nuts.

title: hot german potato salad fondue
directions: Brown bacon and then remove from pan and drain.
Add celery and onion to drippings.
Cook until onion is limp.
Stir in remaining ingredients except potatoes, parsley and bacon.
Cook until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Fold in potatoes, parsley and bacon.
Cover and heat.
Serves 6.

title: squash pudding
directions: Mix together flour and eggs and add to mashed squash.
Add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with nutmeg and cook for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ever so easy fruitcake
directions: Butter a 9-inch tube pan or spring-form pan.
Line with wax paper.
Butter again.
Sift flour and baking soda.
Combine eggs mincemeat, sweetened condensed milk, fruit and nuts.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a slow (300°) oven for two hours until center springs back when lightly touched and top is golden.
Cool.
Turn out of pan and remove paper.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Use a big iron skillet.
Mix corn meal, sweet milk, cream-style corn, salt, baking soda and eggs together; set aside. Brown ground chuck and red cayenne pepper; drain (keep grease). Mix grease into meal mixture (optional).
Brown 1/2 teaspoon corn meal with 1 tablespoon grease in skillet.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Prepare pudding with milk as directed on package.
Spoon into crusts.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs over pudding to cover.
Push licorice legs into pudding, 8 per spider.
Press eyes into place. Makes 6 chocolate spiders.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar together.
Spread out in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake
8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzels and chill.
Boil water; add Jell-O.
Add frozen strawberries.
Chill.
Pour over cream cheese when chilled.
Refrigerate until set.

title: bunuelos(mexican fritters)
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture all at once and stir just until dough sticks together.
On a floured surface, knead dough until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 30 minutes.
Divide dough into 24 portions and shape into balls. Roll each ball on a floured surface into a 4-inch circle.
Heat 1/2 to 1-inch of oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Fry each circle for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side or until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Add beets with juice, sliced onion and peeled eggs.
Add water to cover eggs.
Refrigerate.
Prepare at least 24 hours before serving for best flavor.

title: chocolate delight pie
directions: Pour pudding over cream cheese mixture.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle a few nuts on top.

title: fried rice and ham
directions: Place eggs, pepper and soy sauce in small bowl.
Stir slightly and set aside.
Heat wok or pan hot and dry.
Add oil.
Brown garlic and ginger slightly, then add rice.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring to break up lumps.
Add meat and vegetables.
Fry and stir constantly until thoroughly heated.
Add the egg mixture while stirring rice so it will cover as much as possible.
Stir constantly while cooking until egg mixture begins to firm, about 2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: aunt marm's cornmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put into a pie crust and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes (or until knife inserted comes out clean).

title: cheese rice casserole
directions: Mix all but cheese together.
Pour into a 2-quart flat casserole, then spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Very good with steak.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Saute onion in oleo until tender. In large bowl, mix soups, milk and cheese.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Divide into 2 (2 1/2-quart) casseroles.
Bake at 350° until rice is done (45 to 50 minutes).

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Have head and stomach removed.
Leave bone in; wash well. Make slashes on top of fish.
Fill with 1/8 teaspoon pepper, chopped fine garlic and chopped fine parsley.
Place under broiler.

title: beef party ball
directions: Place cream cheese, onions, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and 2/3 of dried beef into mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed. Shape mixture into a ball and coat with remaining dried beef. Serve with crackers.
Yield:
1 (16 ounce) ball.

title: texas taters
directions: Thaw potatoes.
In a large bowl combine potatoes, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, onion, 1/2 cup of margarine and salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend first four ingredients with fork.
Roll in nuts.
Store wrapped in foil in refrigerator.

title: scalloped cauliflower
directions: Cook the cauliflower in boiling, salted milk and water until tender, using the milk to keep the cauliflower white; drain and break the vegetable into small pieces.
Heat the butter and cream together and add seasoning and nuts.
Grease a baking dish and sprinkle it with crumbs; put in a layer of cauliflower, then a little of the sauce, more cauliflower and more sauce, until the dish is filled or the ingredients used.
Sprinkle the remainder of the crumbs on top and place in a hot oven to brown.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Remove chicken from the bones and arrange in a dish.
Combine the soup and the milk.
Pour over the chicken.
Top with prepared dressing.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix as any other ice cream.
Freeze in electric ice cream maker. This makes two freezers full.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes. Be careful not to overbake.
Cool.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
When partially set, whip until creamy.
Add mayonnaise, cottage cheese, cucumber and onion. Mix well.
Set overnight.
(Very good with ham.)

title: kiddie-ritas
directions: In blender, mix together the orange and lime juices and sugar. Add ice and blend for several minutes until you get a slushy consistency.
For the glass frosting, wet the rims of the glasses and dip them into a plate of powdered sugar.
Fill the cups 2/3 full; top each with a paper mini parasol (optional) and serve.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients until dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: indian taco shells
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook as you would a pancake, the thinner, the better.
Fill with your own taco recipe.

title: fried chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, one piece at a time; shake to coat.

title: crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Layer saltines on foil-lined 15 x 10-inch pan.
Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour or spoon mixture over saltines. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes (watch carefully).
Remove from oven and spread chips over top of saltines.
(Using back of spoon helps.)
Don't let cool at all or chips won't melt.
You can do it right on oven doors so the syrup on the crackers is still liquid hot.
Cool in refrigerator then break into pieces.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Fry hamburger or can substitute with 2 cups cooked and diced chicken
and onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste. Drain fat.
Add soup, milk and peppers; mix well.

title: crispy chocolate drops
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate pieces over low heat; stir constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in rice cereal and chopped nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 40.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water; drain water.
Put milk, cheese and flour in blender.
Add mixture to broccoli.
Add cream.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium heat until mixture thickens.

title: granny hale's date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the brown sugar, margarine and egg.
Add baking soda in water to creamed mixture. Add chopped dates to creamed mixture.
Mix nuts in flour and add to mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: best play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients over low heat until heated through.
Let cool, then knead.
Knead well before each use.

title: corn casserole
directions: *Don't drain off water.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350°.
Test at 40 minutes, may take longer.
Enjoy!

title: creamy dill rice salad
directions: Combine rice and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add dressing and toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Stir in bacon before serving.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; add sugar, flour, beaten eggs and margarine.
Cook until thick.
Let cool slightly; pour over pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Serve cold.
Serves 5.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating well. Mix flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Add flavorings.
Beat well.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: baked chow mein casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole and cover with the crushed potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cream cake
directions: Whip cream stiff.
Add salt and slowly add sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add alternately with water to whipped cream mixture.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Bake in layers at 375°.
Put layers together with your favorite vanilla, coconut or lemon filling.
Frost with Angel Icing.

title: grandma knatsous' doughnuts
directions: In a bowl, mix together egg, sugar, butter, sour milk or buttermilk and vanilla.
Add salt, nutmeg, soda, baking powder and flour.
Stir well. Roll out onto floured board to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in hot lard, turning as soon as they rise to surface. Turn often until done.
Makes 30 to 36 doughnuts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard or Crisco.
Add eggs.
Dissolve soda in raisin water and add.
Add flour, oatmeal and nuts.

title: 4 flavors pound cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar for 5 minutes (this is very important).
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour with salt alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Beat well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a tube pan that has been greased on the bottom only.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Simmer for 2 hours.

title: wedding drink
directions: Blend together until mixed well.
Makes one blender full. Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese and condensed milk until creamy.
Add powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into two 9-inch pie crusts and freeze.

title: breakfast burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture by tablespoonfuls into 2-inch patties.
Cook in skillet over medium-high heat, about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture with bananas.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Add sugar, water and cherries.
Let it come to a boil.
Pour over Jell-O.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Stir well.
Add Coke and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: parsleyed rice
directions: Bring water to a boil with salt.
Add rice; stir until water returns to boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Drain rice and rinse in colander.
Set rice in colander over boiling water.
Cover rice with lid.
Steam 15 minutes or until fluffy and dry.
In large bowl, toss parsley with rice and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and dice medium onion; barely cover in water.
Add salt and pepper.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add butter, cheese, egg and sour cream or cottage cheese.
Mix and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs with a little melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: Boil last 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour boiled mixture over shredded cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Let cool. Refrigerate overnight.

title: filet de atun(tuna steaks)
directions: Rub tuna steaks with salt, pepper and dill.
Heat olive oil in a heavy skillet and pan-fry tuna steaks over high heat, 3 minutes per side.
Remove tuna to baking dish and set aside.
Pour off oil in the skillet so that only 1 tablespoon remains.
Saute onion, peppers, parsley and remaining spices until they are just cooked. Pour sauce over tuna in baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with fresh, chopped parsley and boiled new potatoes.

title: nan's pickled okra
directions: Trim stems off okra leaving caps on. Place dill seeds, pepper, and garlic in bottom of 1 qt. canning jar. Place pods of okra in jar. Bring vinegar, water, and salt to a hard boil; pour over okra. Seal jar while hot. Store at least 2 months before using.

title: bread (easy egg braid)
directions: In bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Heat water, milk and shortening until warm (shortening does not need to melt), then add to flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir
remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic at least 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Fold Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip; add cherry pie filling, coconut and pineapple.
Put pecans and cherries on top.
Chill.

title: karen's version of marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all cans of vegetables.
In a bowl, mix in corn.
In saucepan, heat the vinegar, water, oil and sugar to a boil.
Pour the mixture over the vegetables.
Stir with a wooden or plastic spoon.
Refrigerate for about 24 hours.
Wonderful and colorful.

title: grandma's lima beans
directions: Soak dried limas overnight in water.
The next day, drain off the water.
Cover with fresh water and add 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook until tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Drain again.
Rinse under hot water and put in medium casserole.
Add butter.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl and mix in lima beans lightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend all ingredients, except crabmeat, 1/2 cup cheese and paprika in blender.
Fold in crabmeat and put in serving dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve warm with mild crackers, bagel chips, pita chips, or French bread slices.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together cocoa and flour.
Blend in smooth with butter. Add sugar and milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Serve on hot biscuits.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Whip cream cheese, vanilla or almond extract and 1/3 cup sugar until creamy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Spread with fresh fruit. Drain pineapple or fruit cocktail.
Add water to make 1 cup juice. Add cornstarch, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Boil 1 minute to thicken.
Cool.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: gotta salami with walnuts
directions: Mix walnuts and cream cheese (soften cheese first).
Fill into salami.
Roll.
Stick a toothpick to hold.

title: fresh lemon ice cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine half and half and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Freeze several hours until firm.
To serve, garnish with lemon twists.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Put can salmon in pie pan.
Remove most of juice, bones and skin.
Mash with fork in mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 grated or chopped onion, 2 eggs, 2 dashes Worcestershire sauce and enough flour or meal to thicken.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Divide butter in thirds and put in bowl of ice.
Put enough water in bottom part of double boiler so that it is not touching top part of double boiler.
Bring water to a gentle boil.
In top of double boiler mix egg yolks and lemon juice.
Spear 1/3 of butter with a fork and swish it around in the lemon-egg mixture until melted.
Immediately spear another 1/3 of butter and repeat until all butter is melted.
Remove from stove, season and serve. Frozen butter can be use.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter; beat in sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Roll in palm of hand the size of a butter ball.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: can't beat me coffee cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix salt, flour, and shortening as pie crust.
Soak 1 pkg. yeast in warm water and add a little sugar.
Then combine warm milk eggs and vanilla.
Mix ingredients for all three mixtures together.
Refrigerate overnight or when needed.
Divide dough. Let rise 2 hours before baking.

title: sliced tomatoes and cucumbers
directions: Skin tomatoes and chill.
Peel and thinly slice cucumber and onion.
Cut tomatoes into thick slices.
Arrange in salad bowl with cucumber and onion.

title: tossed spinach salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine spinach, mushrooms, bacon, celery, cheese, eggs and onions. In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine the remaining ingredients; shake until sugar is dissolved. Drizzle over salad and toss to coat. Serve immediately. Yields 12 servings.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer in casserole:
uncooked rice and drained corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce plus 1/2 cup water over. Add finely chopped onion and bell pepper.
Add ground beef (uncooked).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over second can tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover with bacon, cut in half. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Preheat oven 350° Cut each slice of buttered bread in half, leaving crust on.
Layer bread on the bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle the peel and half the currrants. Cover with another layer of buttered bread.
Add the remaining currants. Mix milk and cream, stir in sugar and lemon. Wisk eggs in seperate bowl.
The add them to the milk mixture. Pour over bread. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake for 30-40 min. Serve Warm.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and slice in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Mix milk and egg.
Beat slightly with fork.
Dip eggplant slices into egg mixture and the cracker crumbs.
Fry at medium heat until lightly brown.
Salt lightly.
Arrange browned slices in a 2 or 3-quart casserole dish. Cut cheese slices in quarters and arrange them on top of the eggplant slices.
Spoon half of the undiluted mushroom soup on top of the cheese.
Repeat for next layer.
Finish with a few cracker crumbs for topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy enchilada(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat tortillas 30 to 45 seconds.
Place 1/3 cup filling in each.
Place tortillas in oblong dish.
Cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda and salt into first mixture.
Fold in quick oats and then cornflakes.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Makes a dishpan full.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix eggs with salt, pepper, onion and garlic powder in wide soup dish; also use a wide soup dish for crumbs.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove 1 cup of the dry cake mix; reserve.
Beat 1 egg in small bowl.
In large bowl, stir remaining cake mix, 1/2 cup melted butter and beaten egg.
Press into prepared pan.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and shortening until light and fluffy. Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour, that has been sifted with baking powder, alternately with milk.
Add flavorings; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan and adding glaze.

title: salted pecans
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add pecans and salt.
Stir well to coat pecans.
Remove from heat.
Place pecans into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour and stir every 15 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: lemon cake
directions: Put ingredients in bowl and beat 5 minutes at medium speed. Pour into 10 x 13-inch greased pan.
Put in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Boil ingredients, except nuts, for 10 minutes.
Stir in nuts and cool.

title: japanese shrimp sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Use over shrimp and rice, or baked chicken and rice.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Combine butter and flour in saucepan over low heat; add milk gradually.
Add salt and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Line baking dish with crumbs; add layers of crab meat, cheese and white sauce.
Repeat layers until used up.
Place crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream drops
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add vanilla and sour cream; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with honey wine sauce
directions: In bowl, mix soy sauce, wine and garlic powder; add chicken and marinate 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain chicken.
Save marinade liquid.
In dish, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
In frypan, heat oil; add chicken and brown chicken approximately 10 minutes.
Add honey to marinade liquid; pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken to serving dish; spoon sauce over chicken when serving.

title: breakfast pie(breakfast)
directions: Brown sausage until done, drain and set aside.
Lightly butter bottom and sides of dish.
Arrange bread cubes in dish to cover bottom; set aside.
Pour drained sausage over bread cubes; spread evenly.
Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Pour this mixture over sausage and bread cubs.
Cover to let settle overnight (meat and cheese will float to top).

title: green beans almondine
directions: In large skillet over high heat, bring 1-inch water to a boil.
Add washed green beans and cook 5 minutes; drain.
Remove beans and wipe out skillet.
In the same skillet over medium-high heat, melt the butter.
Add sliced almonds; cook 2 minutes or until browned, stirring frequently.
Meanwhile, halve the cherry tomatoes.
Add to skillet and cook 3 to 5 minutes, gently pressing with a wooden spoon to release the juices.
Season tomato mixture with salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes more or until softened.
Add cooked green beans to the skillet.
Gently toss all ingredients together; cook 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and milk; beat again.
Add Cool Whip and blend together. Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze until ready to serve. Add curls or sauce for garnish when serving.

title: dill and nasturtium bud vinegar
directions: Bring vinegar to boil.
Place nasturtium buds and sprig of fresh dill in a crock, stainless steel or enamel pot and pour the boiling vinegar over them.
Cover and allow to steep for 1 week.

title: weight watchers strawberry corn pancakes
directions: Using fork, combine cornmeal, flour and baking powder in medium bowl.
In small bowl, combine milk, egg and vanilla.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture and stir.
Gently fold in 1/2 cup strawberries using rubber spatula.
In 9-inch nonstick skillet, melt 2 teaspoons margarine.
Drop batter into skillet (1/4 cup) making 4 pancakes, leaving space between each.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes until golden.
Turn and cook 1 more minute.
Repeat using margarine and batter to make 4 more.
To serve, top each pancake with remaining strawberries.

title: three bean salad
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Mix in a small bowl all other ingredients and pour over the beans.
Let stand for 12 hours, stirring every 2 to 3 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread the popcorn on baking sheets and set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Boil for 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add baking soda, vanilla and salt. Stir thoroughly.
The mixture will "foam."
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Bake in a 250° oven for 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes to coat popped corn.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, cool and cut into pieces.
Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole and layer chicken on bottom, onions, chips and cheese.
Top with soup and tomatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Add soup on top of meat.
Put cheese on top of soup.
Put Tater Tots on top of cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until Tater Tots are brown.

title: pollo frito(fried chicken)
directions: Rinse chicken pieces under cold running water and pat dry with paper towels.
Put the garlic, peppercorns, salt and oregano into a mortar and pound until crushed.
Rub this seasoning thoroughly into the chicken pieces, including the liver, gizzard and neck.

title: vienna potato salat
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and slice.
Then add onions, salt, pepper and chopped eggs.
Put in salad and add mayo.
Chop 4 small dill pickles and add 1/4 cup of pickle juice; toss.
Let stand 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble 1/2 pound ground beef in 2 1/2-quart casserole; add salt to taste.
Add one-half of sliced potatoes, then a layer of peas.
Spread noodles over peas.
Add remaining potatoes.
Salt to taste.
Cover with remaining ground beef.
Pour onion soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Cook all together till it thickens, except the eggs.
Cool the pudding.
Add the beaten eggs and stir.
Whipped cream on it is very good. You can also use it to put in a pie crust.

title: rosalynn carter's flank steak(former president jimmy carter's wife)
directions: Combine soy sauce and wine in a shallow dish.
Marinate flank steak for 1 hour or longer in mixture, turning occasionally.

title: sweet pork chops and beans baked
directions: Heat oven at 325°.
Pour baked beans into 9 x 12-inch pan. Lay pork chops on top of the baked beans.
Pour Karo syrup on top, until empty.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pasta in pot
directions: Boil shells as directed.
Brown hamburg; drain all fat.
Mix hamburg with tomato sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 hamburg mixture.
After layering half of the shells on bottom of pan, add Provolone slices.
Pour all the sour cream over this mixture.
Put slices of Mozzarella on top.
Cover with foil; bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients to make base.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 4 tablespoons creme de menthe for 3 minutes and bake as directed.
Let cool.

title: baked apricots
directions: Put layer of apricots in a greased casserole.
Cover with brown sugar and crushed crackers.
Repeat and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt, celery, eggs, onion and soup and put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan (not metal). Before baking, top with the following in the order as given: almonds, Cheddar cheese and potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400° or for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: great beef and onions
directions: Saute beef, mushrooms and onion in butter or oleo.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup water.
Let simmer over low heat until meat and mushrooms are tender.
Add soup mix while simmering.
Add sour cream.
Stir until mixed. Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles and any green vegetable.

title: springtime spaghettini
directions: Bring water to rapid boil in large saucepan.
Add salt and pasta.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into baking pan.
Bake, covered, in slow oven (325°) for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Uncover the last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat 1/4 cup margarine and 1/4 cup shortening in oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches in 425° oven until melted.
Place coated chicken skin sides down in pan.
Cook uncovered 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; cook about 30 minutes longer.
Cut chicken into pieces; cut each breast half into halves.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a brown paper sack.
Place chicken pieces in sack and shake to coat.

title: lemon-sage broth
directions: Pour the broth into a 4 cup measure.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes, or until it comes to a boil.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and let the soup steep for at least 5 minutes.
If necessary, reheat on High for 1 or 2 minutes before serving.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, melted shortening and vanilla.
Pour in greased square pan.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour warm water over batter.
Do not mix.
Bake.
Pudding settles on bottom and brownies are on top.
Great with Dream Whip while warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop corned beef into small pieces and set aside. Chop green onion and combine with cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce. Add chopped corned beef to cheese mixture, setting aside a small amount to sprinkle on top when finished. Chill and serve in your favorite dish.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over peeled, hard-cooked eggs and let stand two or three days before ready to serve.
Really good.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion in skillet.
Add ground beef and seasonings.
Cook until ground beef is brown and crumbly; drain.
Add green beans and soup, stirring gently.
Add milk and egg to potatoes gradually.
Mix well after each addition.
Place ground beef mixture in casserole dish.
Drop potatoes by spoonful onto meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix and store.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: apple caramel dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients (whip or blend in blender).
Dice apples.
Serve dip at room temperature.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in 1-inch boiling water, heat carrots and 1/4 teaspoon salt to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender-crisp, then drain.
In a saucepan, heat butter, sugar, nutmeg and 3/4 teaspoon salt; stir well and heat.
Add carrots; stir until carrots are glazed.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Stir well.
Keep covered in refrigerator at least 1 hour (better overnight).
Dough keeps in refrigerator for a week for use when needed.
Flour hands before forming rolls.
Pinch off enough dough to roll into shape of biscuit.
Place on greased pan and let rise an hour or two at room temperature.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup cheese, chives, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir margarine into hot noodles.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Arrange in dish or platter and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients on low speed.
Put in buttered dish.

title: italian slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Layer in large bowl, alternating cabbage with slices of onion.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over top of cabbage.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Cover and let sit at room temperature 6 to 8 hours or overnight, then stir and refrigerate.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed on box.
When done, use large meat fork to put holes all in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake; cool completely.
Mix cream of coconut and Cool Whip.
Put on cake.
Put shredded coconut on top of cake.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Gets more moist each day.

title: rich sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar, egg, butter and vanilla well. Sift flour, soda, salt and tartar.
Combine. Roll into 1 teaspoon size balls. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare cake as per directions on box.
Mix pie glaze and strawberries together.
After cake has completely cooled, frost with strawberry glaze mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop each ingredient coarsely in food processor. (Use peeling of orange and apple.)
Add sugar and pineapple.
Chill overnight.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside. Cream butter and sugars; add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.
Eat and enjoy.
A perfect treat for the Halloween season.

title: jewish bars
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour, cocoa and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° on a 10 x 14-inch greased cookie sheet with rim for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread can of condensed milk over hot cake.
Spread coconut over milk. Bake another 15 minutes; let cool.
Spread cream cheese frosting over cookie.
Cut into bars.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans for 5 minutes. Arrange pecans on bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Pour in batter and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from oven and pierce top thoroughly with a toothpick.
Immediately pour glaze over top. Cool completely before removing cake from pan.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread evenly with sour cream.
Pour remaining gelatin atop.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 9 squares.
I sometimes omit the strawberries and add more bananas.
When you do this, you must add 1 3/4 cups cold water.

title: cherry chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, add cake mix, pie filling, extract and eggs by hand, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into pan, bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Boil chicken and tear into pieces.
Roll chicken in crescent rolls; bake.
Spread cream of chicken soup on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Melt the cheese.

title: all the year round cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and the powdered sugar.
Beat in the boiling water.
Add the eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with the cold water; beat well.
Add vanilla.
May be baked as a layer or loaf cake.

title: chicken pasta dish
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° for 45 minutes or until cooked. Boil twists for 15 minutes or until cooked.
Steam broccoli for approximately 20 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain spinach. Add onion soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: flying pizza saucers(kids' stuff)
directions: Split muffins in half; top with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle on oregano or basil.
Cover with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: cinnamon carrots
directions: Stir together cornstarch, tomato juice, brown sugar and cinnamon in a 2-quart saucepan.
Over medium heat, stir mixture until it boils and thickens. Add carrots.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: On low to medium heat on stove, melt butter.
Stir in flour until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients except chives.
Stir constantly until smooth and creamy.
Add chives.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Spread in plate.
Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar and Karo syrup for 5 1/2 to 6 minutes on High.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Pour into greased pan and press down.
Cut in squares.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt cheese with 1/2 stick margarine. Pour over cooked carrots and mix.
Melt 1 stick margarine and add Ritz crackers.
Brown well.
Put on top of carrots.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chili ham pinwheels
directions: Remove crusts from loaf of bread.
Then cut it in thin slices lengthwise of the loaf.
Spread lightly with butter, then with the ham and chili sauce, mixed together.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until soft and fluffy.
Gradually add flour until well mixed.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Roll, shape or put in cookie press; bake at 400° for 7 minutes.

title: ube jam
directions: Combine Carnation evaporated milk, ube and sugar.
Cook over a low flame until thick.
Keep on stirring to prevent scorching.

title: pecan chess bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat at low speed until crumbly.
Stir in pecans, press into the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 12 inch dish.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes until edges are browned.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: In double boiler, cook sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks until thickened.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in vanilla and evaporated milk.
Place in freezer and fill outer freezer 1/3 full of ice.
Using six parts ice to one part coarse rock salt, layer until freezer is full.
Turn crank slowly for five minutes, then rapidly until crank becomes hard to turn.
Remove dasher from cream; re-cover.
Pour off any water; pack with ice.
Allow to stand 1/2 hour before serving, to allow it to harden completely and for flavor to develop.

title: quick and good cobbler
directions: Mix egg, Bisquick, sugar and margarine with just enough milk to make a cake-like batter.
Put a small amount of butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and place in a 350° oven.
When it starts to sizzle, pour batter in pan and put fruit on top.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chili cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add beaten eggs and other wet ingredients. Pour into 9 x 15 inch baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift in flour and cinnamon.
Add carrots, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into floured, greased loaf pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Freezes well.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
Saute vegetables.
Simmer meat and vegetables and seasonings.
In top of double boiler, melt cheese.
Add tomatoes. Put lettuce and fresh, diced tomatoes in large bowl.
Add the meat mixture and toss lightly.
Add corn chips.
Top with cheese mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with dill pickles and/or tomatoes on the side.

title: princess pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk together.
Add orange, cocktail and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: manicotti with cheese filling
directions: Cook manicotti shells in 4 quarts boiling salted water for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients (less the manicotti shells and spaghetti sauce) in a large mixing bowl.
Stuff each shell with 1/3 to 1/2 cup filling.
Pour enough spaghetti sauce to cover bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Lay shells side by side.
Pour remaining sauce over the shells. Sprinkle the top with Parmesan cheese, if desired and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix together and let stand for 3 hours the pears, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, clove, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Add eggs to pear mixture.
Then add the nuts.
Cook in tube pan for one hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together cream cheese and butter, then add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add more milk or sugar for right consistency.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown meat on both sides in hot shortening.
Top with onions and tomatoes.
Cover.
Cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add green pepper.
Cook 15 minute more.
Skim off excess fat.
Thicken juices, if desired.
Season to taste.

title: deep fried catfish
directions: Select several fresh catfish fillets. Set aside. Put oil in deep pan or wok 3 - 4 inches deep. Heat oil until it just starts to smoke.
Mix paprika and flour together in shallow dish.
In separate dish whip eggs and milk together. Dip fillets in egg mixture then dredge with flour.
Slowly lower fillets in hot oil. Don't drop in oil.
Deep fry to a golden brown or fish starts to flake.
Garnish with lemon slice.

title: kentucky hot brown
directions: Place ham and turkey on toast.
Pour on Cheese Sauce.
Place tomato and bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with cheese.
Makes 1 Hot Brown.

title: cinnamon rolls made easy
directions: Dissolve yeast in water approximately 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup of flour, oil, eggs and salt.
Beat with beater until bubbles appear.
Slowly stir in rest of flour.
Stir with a spoon, making a soft dough.
Knead on board for 5 minutes.
Let rise until double.

title: fettuccine with spicy tomato cream sauce
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium-low heat.
Add onion and red pepper and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and salt.
Cook over high heat, crushing tomatoes with spoon, until almost dry, about 8 minutes.
Stir in cream and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough as for cookies; place in pizza pan.
Bake as directed to a golden brown.
Mix the cream cheese and whipped topping at room temperature.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit in rings over cream cheese mixture.
Pour sauce over mixture. Refrigerate.
Cut in slices like pizza.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Heat oil (1/4 inch) in a large skillet.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.

title: quick cardamon coffee cake
directions: Mix first
4 ingredients.
Stir in 1 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until
particles are the size of peas.
Add milk and stir
quickly
until
blended.
Spread
in well-greased 9-inch square
pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixed with sugar.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.	Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: city chicken
directions: You will also need wood skewers.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, rind and milk.
Then add flour, baking powder and nuts.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
While still warm, glaze with a mixture of juice of 1 lemon and 1/3 cup granulated sugar.

title: cornbread or corn muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine milk, butter and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until blended. Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased baking pan or greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: white bean and tomato salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine garlic, onion, celery, lemon juice, olive oil, mint or basil, tomatoes and salt and pepper in a plastic bowl with airtight top.
Add beans and carefully stir with a wooden spoon so beans won't break apart.
Serves four.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown onions and garlic in butter.
Add meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: cheese drops
directions: Divide each biscuit into fourths.
Take cubes of cheese and mold biscuit dough around each cube.
Make sure to close all gaps of dough (this will keep cheese from melting out).
Heat deep fryer until hot.
Drop cheese drops into oil and cook until light brown.
Remove and serve warm or cool.

title: rachel's barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: corn a la king
directions: Mix corn, peppers and milk in double boiler and add beaten egg and seasoning.
Cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hot buttered toast.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, drain.
In a skillet, place carrots and remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until carrots are glazed and glossy.
Serves 6.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 350°
oven.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: rice pudding(microwave)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix with rice.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Cook 5 minutes on High speed.
Serves 6.

title: freezer jam
directions: Cook first three ingredients until mashed, about 10 minutes. Add jello.
Put in freezer containers and freeze until served.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Line 10-inch pan with pastry.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 400°. Cook onion in butter until transparent.
Mix with ham.
Beat eggs and egg yolk, light cream and seasonings.
Add to ham mixture. Pour into pastry shell.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: southwest chicken with salsa
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine chicken broth and 1 cup salsa.
Pour all but 1 cup of this mixture over rice and stir to combine.
Arrange chicken halves over rice mixture.
Pour remaining salsa mixture over the chicken.
Cover dish with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Lift chicken off rice and stir in frozen peas.
Return chicken. Top with remaining salsa and shredded cheese.
Return to oven covered and bake 30 more minutes or until chicken is done and liquid is absorbed.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, beating well after each egg.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mound apples in a buttered pie plate or casserole.
Sprinkle with orange juice.

title: kiwi christmas tree
directions: You will need one large cookie sheet, covered with foil, for this recipe.

title: sugar-free spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour. Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour in greased 9 x 11-inch or about pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: meatballs in italian sauce
directions: Blend together ground beef, 1/8 teaspoon garlic, eggs, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Shape into small balls, allowing 3 tablespoons for each.
Roll in flour and pan-fry until well browned.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Brown meat and sausage and add the cheese and spices. Cook until cheese melts.
Spread thick on bread and bake ten minutes at 400°.

title: mamma's lemon pie
directions: Prepare crust or use store bought.
Mix juice of lemons or lemon juice with water.
Stir together in medium saucepan sugar, flour and salt.
Pour in lemon water, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg white, cream of tartar and cold water until it peaks.
Spoon onto pie.
Bake to golden brown on top at 375°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, nuts and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine berries, sugar, lemon and egg whites.
Beat on high speed for 20 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Remove 1/3 cup crumb mixture from pan.
Pat remaining crumbs into a smooth layer. Pour berry mixture over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Freeze.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter in bowl; mix well with fork. Add egg; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet; press with tines of fork.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
While potatoes are cooking, fry bacon and onion.
Break bacon up in small pieces.
Add to potatoes.
Stir well and add 1 can evaporated milk and cream-style corn.
Stir in salt and pepper to taste.
Now add enough regular milk until chowder is desired thickness.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put 2 tablespoons olive oil in pot.
Add about 4 cloves garlic and sausage.
Brown meat.
Add other ingredients and water.
Stir to even boil.
Turn down on low.
Simmer 4 hours.
Stir about every 15 minutes (with a bubble every now and then).

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and add spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle herb seasoning in hamburger mixture; set aside.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut lettuce and cauliflower fine and layer in bowl with onion. Add sugar, cheese and bacon.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Let stand overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
In medium size serving bowl, layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.
Chill thoroughly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain and peel.
Add other ingredients.
Blend with mixer until smooth.
Pour in Pyrex dish.

title: baked barbecued ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ribs; set aside for 1 hour. Cut every third rib; salt lightly. Place ribs in shallow roasting pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Drain off fat; cover with sauce and bake for 1 1/2 hours longer or until tender.

title: zucchini-squash-tomato casserole
directions: Slice and saute in olive oil with chopped onion and chopped garlic cloves.
Cook fast (not more than 5 minutes), stirring and shaking.
Put in casserole dish; pat down (even out).
Cover with thinly sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons fresh basil or parsley.
Pour on 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Put under broiler 3 to 4 minutes or until light brown.

title: zurich geschnetzeltes
directions: Saute the thinly sliced veal on all sides in very hot butter. Remove from the pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper and keep warm. Slightly reduce the heat, then finely chop the onion and add to the fat from the meat.
Saute briefly, then pour in the wine. Simmer until the liquid is reduced by 1/2.
Add cream; bring to a boil.
Add the meat juices; season with salt, pepper and a few drops of lemon juice.
Reheat the meat in the sauce, but do not let it boil.
Serve topped with parsley.

title: congealed pistachio salad
directions: Mix well together.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
Chill until set.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Keep 1 cup dry cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Press into bottom and 3/4 way up sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry onions and hamburger.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: corned beef "n" cabbage hash
directions: Saute the potatoes in oil in large, nonstick skillet over medium heat, stirring often, until tender and lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Add the onions; saute 1 minute longer.
Add cabbage, corned beef, caraway seed, pepper and salt.
Mix well.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil sugar, butter, syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda and butter flavoring.
Stir well into popcorn. Bake in oven at 100° for about 1 hour, stirring about every 15 minutes until dry.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in large heavy skillet.
Drain any fat.
Add onions, celery, carrots, garlic, tomatoes, tomato sauce, kidney beans, water, bouillon, parsley, salt, oregano, basil and pepper. Bring to boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add 2 cups shredded cabbage, 1 cup frozen or fresh green beans (cut in 1-inch pieces) and 1/2 cup small elbow macaroni.
Bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix cornbread mix to package directions and bake.
Mix remaining ingredients and crumble cornbread; mix well.
Mixture should be soupy (if needed, add water to make soupy).
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until done and golden brown.
(If desired, 1 box wild rice can be added.)

title: "bravo" potatoes
directions: In a large nonstick skillet heat olive oil over medium-high heat until it shimmers.
Fry cubed potatoes in a single layer until browned and partially cooked through, about 10 minutes.
Turn once or twice with a spatula, but don't stir too often - they'll brown better if left alone.
Pulse tomatoes, garlic and seasonings in food processor just to break up tomatoes (do not puree).
After potatoes have browned, add tomato mixture and stir to coat.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted butter.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.
Next, mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup whipped topping.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Spread on top of second layer.
Spread whipped topping and sprinkle with crushed cookies.

title: marilyn's brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Soak brisket in marinade for 24 hours.
Bake in ungreased shallow pan, covered for 4 or 5 hours in 300° oven or until tender.
Slice thinly and put back in marinade and bake 1 hour longer.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, soda and other ingredients. Drop on greased pan and bake in slow 300° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix small amount of the 3 cups of flour with chopped fruits and nuts.
Good Christmas cookies.

title: avocado dish salad
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Stir in garlic powder, garlic salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Carefully spread sour cream over mixture.
Drain picante sauce and spoon on top of sour cream being careful not to mix in with sour cream layer.
Layer chopped, ripe olives over picante sauce.
Layer chopped tomatoes over olives.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: Saute
onion
and
pepper in 2 tablespoons of oleo in a large pan.
Add
all soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and 1 full can of water; stir
to
dissolve.
Break or cut tortillas into small pieces
and line
bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan. Layer
chicken, soup mix, tortillas, etc., until all ingredients
are
used.
Top with
sliced
cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Fry ground beef until browned.
Drain very well.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix well and add refried beans.
Place in a baking dish.
Add a small amount of Cheddar cheese on top.
Mix sour cream, green chilies and red salsa together.
Spread over cheese. Spread rest of cheese over entire dish.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese is lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips.
Very good.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour on top of rice.
Place breasts on this and sprinkle with soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; stir halfway through cooking time.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook and drain lasagne noodles according to package directions.
For filling: Steam spinach until limp.
Add and mix well 2 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese, 1/2 tsp. nutmeg.
For topping:
Prepare onions and cheeses. For sauce: Combine in a bowl:
tomato sauce, garlic, basil oregano, and marjoram.
Spread noodles with filling, roll up and stand on end in greased 9x13 baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese and onions on top. Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy endive soup
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil and reduce heat.
Add endive, onion, potatoes and garlic and simmer until potatoes are cooked. Add olive oil.
Pass soup through a food processor and return it to the stove.
Bring soup to a boil and finish with heavy cream.
When ready to serve, drizzle the top of each bowl with a small amount of good olive oil.

title: sour cream coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Add other ingredients and toss.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix bean dip, cream cheese and sour cream with electric mixer. Spread in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add water and taco seasoning.
Mix and spread over first layer. Sprinkle with chopped tomato and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° only until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: eclair torte
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water, butter and salt to a boil.
Add flour all at once; stir until smooth ball forms. Remove from heat; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with a wooden spoon after each addition.
Beat until smooth.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine strawberries and lemonade in blender.
Add water and ginger ale.
Pour into punch bowl.
Scoop sherbet into bowl and serve.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve on crackers (Ritz) with cream cheese (Philadelphia).

title: impossible pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; cool.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Add flour, coconut and milk, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Crust forms during baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix by hand 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
