Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove.

title: nutmeg-meltaways
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Stir in the nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Combine confectioners sugar and nutmeg.
Gently roll cooled cookies in sugar mixture.
Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into a ball.
Roll ball in pecans if desired.

title: cream cheese nut tarts
directions: Dough can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Cream together the cream cheese and 1 stick of oleo.
Add 1 cup of flour.
Mix and make into a ball.
Chill.
Filling consists of one beaten egg, to which is added 3/4 cup brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add the salt, vanilla and melted butter; mix.
Then add the chopped nuts.
Mix all together.
Divide the chilled dough into 24 balls.
Each ball makes one tart shell.
Fill at least 1/2 full with filling.
Pan measures 1 3/8 on bottom and 1 7/8 on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until shell is golden brown.
Check after 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake in well-greased pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost.
Drain spinach.
Dry.
Mix all ingredients together and add scallions, salt and pepper.
Cut out center of round loaf of bread and put it in the center.
Cut or break bread to dip in the spinach.

title: candied tomatoes
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer and cook until thick. This is delicious served with vegetables.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together the peanut butter, butter and chocolate chip morsels.
Pour over the cereal.
Mix well, then coat cereal with the powdered sugar.

title: st. charles banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add yolks and beat well . Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas and creamed mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in stiff egg whites gently. Bake at 350° in 2 (9-inch) pans which have been greased for 35 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute onions in olive oil, add celery and saute until tender. Then add minced garlic and fresh basil, saute for about 2 minutes. Add V-8 juice, tomatoes and basil.
Simmer soup for at least 1/2 hour before serving.

title: practically fat-free blue cheese dressing
directions: Place parsley and shallots in bowl of food processor and finely chop.
Add vinegar, oil, mayonnaise, cream cheese, Blue cheese and yogurt.
Add about 1/2 cup of the buttermilk and process until smooth.
Add pepper and remainder of buttermilk and process until well blended.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix 1 cup of nuts, sugar, syrup, vanilla, butter and eggs together.
Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of nuts on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cut 4 slices bread, approximately one-inch thick.
Place in 200° oven until crisp and dry (about an hour).
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions and saute until soft, but not brown (takes about 20 minutes).
Add beef broth, wine, water, thyme, salt and pepper.
Simmer soup, covered, for one hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Spread over warm cake and brown under broiler until bubbly (avoid burning).

title: fruit pizza
directions: Arrange
sliced
cookie
dough	on ungreased pizza pan; bake until
light brown.
Cool.	Mix cheese and sugar; spread over cookies.
Mix
and	drain
fruit cocktail and pineapple; spread over
cheese.
Mix	glaze
and strawberries and spread over fruit. Top with sliced bananas.

title: margaret's rhubarb cake
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Fold in rhubarb. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: bourbon-pecan pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Place pecans in the bottom of the shell.
Pour mixture over the pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cover edges of pie crust with foil strips to prevent crust from being hard and too cooked.

title: kidney bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Allow to set for at least 1 hour.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Drain juices from fruit into saucepan and thicken with sugar, flour and eggs over heat.
Mix with macaroni and set in refrigerator overnight.
Add fruit, Cool Whip, marshmallows and chopped pecans.
Mix well before serving.

title: blueberry, banana dessert(this dessert is delicious!)
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex. Add flour and pecans.
Mix well and spread over bottom of dish. Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Cool.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip by package directions and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over crust.
Top with sliced bananas and cover with blueberry filling. Cover and chill in refrigerator. Cut in squares. Serves 8 or 10.

title: lew's sauteed chicken livers
directions: In a large skillet saute bacon, remove and keep warm.
Add next 4 ingredients, saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and add to bacon. Clean and wash livers.
Pat dry with paper towels.
In the palm of your hand place several livers.
With a sharp fork, prick them several times.
This prevents them from popping.
Repeat until all are done.
Dust with salt and pepper; dust with flour until all are covered.
Heat drippings.
Saute livers a few at a time, just until they are no longer pink in the center.
Do not overcook.
Add bacon, green onions, mushrooms and parsley.
Heat.
Add wine and simmer until wine has evaporated.
If too dry, adjust with hot water.
Serve on slices of hot buttered toast.
Enjoy.

title: strawberry angel food
directions: Put cake
pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream with electric mixer and pour over cake.
Chill.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salt water.
Drain.
Layer in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole the eggplant, tomato slices, onion, pepper and bread crumbs.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Repeat, ending with bread crumbs.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash, onions and peppers. Place in flat pan.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand at least 1 hour.

title: super cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter, sugar and cinnamon in small mixer bowl.
Beat on No. 1 speed until blended evenly. Press mixture, with fingers, firmly to cover bottom and up sides of 9-inch pan.
Wash and dry mixer bowl.

title: orange coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Alternately add flour and milk, beating after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon batter into the 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, approximately, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost while warm (not hot) with the following frosting.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix up Jell-O and let set 1/2 hour.
Drain pineapple and mix in Jell-O mixture.
Put in walnuts.
Ready to eat.

title: out of this world candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; form balls; set in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin; dip balls and set on waxed paper to cool.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown together the onion and ground beef; drain.
Pour contents of all cans together (undrained).
Add beef and simmer at least 30 minutes. Very good for all day in crock-pot!

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Arrange rice in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine the 2 soups and milk in saucepan.
Heat.
Pour over rice and mix.
Arrange chicken over top.
Sprinkle onion soup on if desired.
Cover. Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: beef roast
directions: You will need one browning bag.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Mix all together to make 1 gallon of punch.
Can also be used to make popsicles.

title: breezy brownies and icing
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add salt and eggs.
Blend in chocolate syrup and flour.
Pour in greased 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix and pour over apples. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Slowly blend the ingredients.
Use as many shrimp as you wish.

title: meringue for pies
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Beat in vanilla.
Spread on pies and brown in oven.

title: southern sweet ice tea
directions: Place water, sugar and baking soda in a cooking pot.
Bring to a boil.
Stir, remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover; let steep several hours or overnight.

title: summer squash soup
directions: Steam sliced yellow squash and onion together until tender. Cool and rinse.
Place in a blender and chop using quick pulses. Add 1 cup of additional water to help chop.
(Stop and shake/mix for even, fine chopped consistency.)
(Puree if desired.)

title: microwave chicken and dressing
directions: In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish, toss together stuffing mix, celery, onion, egg and broth.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine.
Place on top of dressing with meaty pieces to outside edge of dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 18 to 22 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quiche
directions: You can add anything you want.
Bake the pie shell until almost done.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Add drained pineapple and orange jello to mixture. Next, add in the drained oranges. Chill.

title: zucchini with a difference
directions: Grate zucchini on coarsest side of grater into large colander. Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Press out as much liquid as possible.
Spray skillet and melt butter.
Add green onions. Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add zucchini.
(If using dry basil, add it now.)
Cook until just tender 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
(If using fresh basil, stir it in with sour cream.) Serves 4.

title: high altitude brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch pan.
Melt butter and chocolate, cool to lukewarm.
Gradually blend in sugar. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and salt to chocolate mix.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan and bake 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
May frost or sprinkle with powdered sugar.
May add 1/2 cup chocolate chips with nuts.
May double recipe and use 9 x 13-inch pan.
If you double just use 3 chocolate squares unless you like it really strong chocolate.

title: yogurt pie
directions: In medium bowl, shake or stir first 3 ingredients.
Add 7-Up; mix and roll.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: pepsi-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries to make 2 cups.
(Add water to make 2 cups, if needed.)
Heat to boil.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Let this cool slightly.
Congeal.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Roll in coconut, nuts or powdered sugar.
Makes 100 small balls.

title: paige's pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In
a large bowl, dissolve yeast in
1 1/2 cups warm water. Add 4 cups flour, lite salt and sugar. Mix well.
On a lightly floured surface, knead the mixture well with your hands.
Roll pieces of dough into any shapes you like. Place them on a
cookie sheet that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
In a small bowl, beat Egg Beater.
Brush the tops of the dough with the Egg Beater. Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake the pretzels at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. This is a great recipe for the kids to make!
Yields 1 1/2 dozen big soft pretzels.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all together and spoon out on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until done, approximately 8 minutes.

title: walnut pastry
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add egg and cold water to make stiff dough.
Chill; roll and bake as for plain pastry.

title: dressing for banana salad
directions: Cook until thickened on low heat.
Let cool, then mix with Cool Whip.
Layer sliced bananas, dressing and ground peanuts. Save enough peanuts to have a layer on top of salad.

title: jam cake and filling
directions: Put baking soda in milk and stir.
Sift other dry ingredients and mix with buttermilk, jam, preserves and eggs.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Make filling and put between layers of cake and ice with a caramel frosting.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix dry milk, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 pounds Nestle Quik, Coffee-mate and powdered sugar together.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat egg; add mayonnaise and soup.
Set this mixture aside in the cooking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix cheese, dressing, onion and broccoli; toss.
Add to egg/soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 or more minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: norwegian gold cake
directions: Mix butter and flour in bowl 5 minutes on high speed.
On low speed, add eggs, one at a time, blending each in turn slowly. Sift sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add extract and Nesselrode.
Mix 2 minutes.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with Pam. Salt and pepper chops on both sides.
Lay in baking dish. Completely cover with ketchup and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: onion bread
directions: Cut bread in 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Brush top and cut sides of bread with butter.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Wrap. Place on grill 20 minutes.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into tarts. Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cut buttered bread slices into cubes.
Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Turn contents of canned mushrooms over bread cubes.
Cut chicken into pieces; spread over mushrooms.
Beat the eggs; combine with the 3 cans of soup (undiluted).
Turn mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Pour pineapple with juice into a bowl. Sprinkle the pudding mix over pineapple. Add sour cream. Mix until well blended. Pour into crust. Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer bacon, lettuce, spinach, celery, onion and peas in salad bowl.
Spread a thick layer of mayonnaise over all and top with grated cheese.
Chill several hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over biscuits.
Put in greased Bundt pan.

title: brandy pecan sauce
directions: Heat topping, nuts and butter, stirring occasionally.
Add brandy.
Cool.
Makes about 2 cups.
Great served over pound cake and ice cream.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly. Cover and chill overnight.
Drain well before serving.

title: microwave cheese puffs
directions: Combine green onions with cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on toast rounds in 8 1/4-inch shallow baking dish.
Heat half the rounds on Medium for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until bubbly.
Turn baking dish once during cooking.
Repeat with remaining puffs. Serve hot.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: mystery cake(1935 date on marie wilson's copy of recipe)
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and grated orange rind.
Add beaten eggs, flour and etc.
Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: louisiana papadums
directions: Slice the bread as thinly as possible.
Dip in the melted butter or brush with melted butter.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 250° until crisp or bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sesame seed or the grated cheese.

title: peanut cream chocolate squares
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and one egg at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Press remaining crumbs in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
In small bowl, blend sugar, peanut butter, cream cheese and 1 egg until smooth.
Gently spread over baked crust.
Combine reserved crumbs and chopped peanuts over filling.
Press lightly.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until firm.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut until bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: low-fat golden potato salad
directions: In large bowl, put potatoes, onion, parsley, celery, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Toss lightly.
Combine milk, mustard, sweetener, vinegar and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a small bowl; beat with a rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Pour over the potato mixture and stir gently until well mixed.
Let stand one hour or longer.
Arrange salad greens in individual salad dishes and arrange 1/2 cup potato salad on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: magic meringue
directions: Boil 1 tablespoon sugar, cornstarch and water together until clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Beat well.
Spoon onto pie filling and brown at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry surprise pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a pie pan.
Stir together cherries, nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Mix oil, salt, 1 cup sugar and flour.
Pour this batter on the cherry mixture.
Cook until cake mixture is brown and firm.

title: broccoli and pea casserole
directions: Cook peas and broccoli. Drain well and combine with soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cover with crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: For a smoother ice cream, separate the eggs and beat the whites until stiff before adding to the mix.
Mix sugar, eggs, milk and ice cream mix.
Add other ingredients. Stir well.
Pour in freezer. Add milk to freezing line.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent roll dough in bottom of jelly roll pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Allow crust to cool.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add dill weed and onion powder.
Spread over crust. Top with carrots, cauliflower, broccoli, green pepper, green onion, fresh mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese.
Serve chilled.

title: barbecued roast
directions: In Dutch oven or roasting pan, brown meat on both sides in 450° oven (10 to 15 minutes per side).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In bowl, crush tomatoes.
Add tuna and mayonnaise.
Put bowl aside.
Boil noodles.
Put soup in saucepan.
Add celery, onion, milk and Cheddar cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted and celery and onion are soft.
Add to tuna mixture.
Pour over noodles and mix.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Cover with crushed chips.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or microwave 10 minutes on High.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seed in oil.
When cool, mix with crushed Ramen noodles (do not use seasoning packet) and set aside. Shred cabbage; add chopped onions and pour following Dressing over. Mix and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; mix with sugar.
Stir in milk.
Pour batter over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour peaches over batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until dark brown on top.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut in half, but do not remove the seeds.
Put on a cookie sheet, cut side up.
Bake at 400° until soft (30 to 45 minutes). Scrape out the seeds and fibers; discard.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put a bit of butter in each; allow 1 or 2 halves per person.

title: sunday chicken casserole
directions: Pour 1/2 of soups in bottom of oiled casserole dish.
Pour in rice and the remainder of soups.
Top with chicken breasts.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 325°.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix 3/4 of cracker crumbs, butter and sugar together to make bottom crust.
Mix Jell-O and water together; set aside.
Whip cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Stir in Jell-O, Cool Whip and strawberries.
Mix all together; top with remaining cracker crumbs.

title: amy's chicken casserole
directions: Melt cheese in microwave until creamy and smooth; add tomatoes, chicken broth and chicken.
Cook spaghetti and blend with cheese mixture.
Keep warm in chafing dish or slow cooker. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: frozen pumpkin squares
directions: Mix and pour over crust.
Freeze. Thaw 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: rice and sour cream
directions: Dissolve bouillon and butter in water.
Add lemon juice, pepper, salt and rice and cook in double boiler for 25 to 30 minutes.
Saute mushrooms in 1/2 stick butter and add it and the sour cream to the rice.

title: tuna cheddar pie
directions: Cook onions, mushrooms and zucchini in margarine until browned.
Sprinkle tuna, 1 cup cheese, and onion mixture into pie plate or square dish.
Beat eggs, milk, baking mix and pepper in blender. Pour over tuna.
Bake 45 minutes at 400° or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Add remaining cheese. Bake 3-5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: it's a sin
directions: Mix margarine, flour and chopped nuts; spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until brown. Cool.

title: arroz mexicano
directions: Soak rice in hot water 10-30 minutes; drain; rinse in cold water; drain.
Heat oil till boiling, cook garlic at the same time.
When oil is boiling, add rice and onion; fry (not stirring frequently) till starts popping; drain oil; add milk, corn, chili, bouillon and 6 cups boiling water.
Cook till water is absorbed (15-20 minutes).
Mix with cheese and cream and pour in
heavily buttered baking dish.
Bake in 350° for 15 minutes or till cheese is melted.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning. Assemble by first spreading bean dip on bottom of serving platter.
Cover with avocado mixture, then spread the sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning mixture over.
Sprinkle on tomatoes and onions and cover with cheese.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Cut phyllo sheets into halves and place 10 pieces in a buttered pan (7 x 11-inch).
Brush each sheet of phyllo with melted butter.
Wash spinach and remove stems.
Cut leaves into 1/2-inch lengths.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 15 minutes.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Take potatoes from freezer and spread in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then melt margarine; add onion, sour cream and soup.
Pour over potatoes, then put cheese on top.
Cover with crumbled potato chips.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: oreo crunch pie
directions: Soften ice cream enough to spread smoothly.
Place ice cream into pie crust until level with top of crust.
Place bite size Oreo cookies side by side around the edge of the crust, then place approximately 3 to 4 cookies in the middle in a circle.
Pour Hershey's chocolate syrup all around.

title: pelican hot chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in quart sauce pan.
Cook over low heat - stir often - until blended and heated thoroughly.
Makes about 7 cups.
This may be served as a dip with crackers or as a main dish over rice. VERY POPULAR AT HAPPY HOUR.

title: tiramisy "pick me up"(a dessert)
directions: Filter 2 tablespoons fine ground coffee until 1/3 cup of boiling water.
Mix together with 3 tablespoons brandy and 1/4 cup coffee liqueur.
Cream together for 5 minutes 1 pound soft Mascarpone cheese, 6 egg yolks and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Fold in 6 beaten egg whites.

title: cucumber relish boats
directions: Peel cucumbers; cut each lengthwise in half.

Into medium bowl, with teaspoon, remove seeds and some pulp from cucumbers to form shells; place shells on serving dish and refrigerate. Coarsely chop cucumber pulp in bowl; stir in 3/4 teaspoon salt and remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin, water and pie filling and chill until firm. Combine remaining ingredients and spread over congealed mixture. Chill until firm.

title: artichoke strata
directions: Saute mushrooms and green onions in margarine until tender (2 or 3 minutes); drain and set aside.
Layer half each of bread cubes, sauteed vegetables, cheese, artichokes and pimento in a lightly greased 9-inch quiche dish.
Repeat layers.

title: best ever gingerbread
directions: Combine all ingredients; add eggs last.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add flour (sifted or not) and vanilla; mix well.
Place by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown around the edges.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light colored; add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden.
Cut into 32 bars.

title: casserole sauce mix
directions: Combine all ingredients
and store in airtight container.
To use as substitute
for
one can of condensed soup, mix 1/3 cup of the mix with
1 1/4 cups water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef and pour off the fat.
Combine the soup, beans and corn and heat in the microwave.
Bake the Tater Tots per pkg. directions.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Mix together the soup/beans/corn mixture and the hamburger, and season to taste. Pour into the casserole dish and spread the Tater Tots over the top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, salt, eggs, milk, chopped onion and pepper well.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar and ketchup together. Add 1/2 of this mixture into the meat loaf mixture.
Baste the top with the remaining part.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: collard greens
directions: Boil meat and seasonings together until meat is tender.
Wash and cut greens into small pieces; remove thick stems.
Add greens to boiling seasoned water.
Cook until tender.
Add extra seasoning to taste if needed.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt until blended.
Melt butter in the milk and heat until lukewarm.
Slowly add enough lukewarm milk to the sugar mixture to make a thin, smooth paste.
Pour the paste back into the milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Slowly pour some of the hot mixture into 6 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Beat into the hot mixture.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; continue to stir while adding the lemon rind and juice.

title: double fudge saucepan brownies
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and water over heat to boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add eggs, vanilla until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt to chocolate chips mixture.
Stir in remaining chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: turkey hash - oven style
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir turkey, potato, evaporated milk, parsley, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt, sage and pepper.
Put mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole.

title: pizza quiche
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 425°.
2. Spread cooking sauce in the bottom of pie crust. Layer
pepperoni over sauce. Sprinkle on all the cheese.
3. In a separate bowl, beat the eggs with the evaporated
milk and seasonings. Pour mixture carefully over the
cheese.
4. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and
bake an additional 55 minutes.
5. When quiche is set, a sharp knife will come out clean
when inserted in the center.
5. After removing from oven wait five minutes before cutting.

title: corn and tomato casserole
directions: Mix.
Warm through in small dish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Batter can be made ahead.
Beat eggs; add sprouts, onion, salt, pepper and fish.
Refrigerate, if desired.

title: ranch pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients; chill thoroughly.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.
Cheese and dressing may be substituted with fat-free versions.

title: micro snack pizzas
directions: Place lid of a gallon jar over bread; cut out circle.
Spread tomato sauce evenly over circle.
Sprinkle cheese and add pepperoni.
Sprinkle more cheese.
Place on microwave-safe plate. Heat on High 1 1/2 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Pre-heat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large bowl blend cake mix, sour cream, granulated sugar, water and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 2/3 of the batter in a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan.
Sprinkle filling ingredients over batter in pan. Spread remaining batter evenly over filling mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45-55 minutes, until cake springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.
Drizzle with glaze made from confectioners sugar mixed with milk.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease round casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
If top is soft, cook another 5 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Cube bread and spread in bottom of pan.
Cover with 1 cup of cheese.
Cook 1 pound of sausage and drain.
Place sausage over cheese layer.
Add another cup of cheese over sausage.
Mix beaten eggs, milk and mustard. Pour over sausage and cheese mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to finish, mix 1/2 cup milk and celery soup.
Pour over all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's chili
directions: Bring all ingredients to a slow boil, except the meatballs. Add meat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: 1-2-3-4 pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately, adding baking powder and salt with last of the flour.
Add flavoring and beat at medium speed until thoroughly mixed.
Put mixture in greased and floured tube/regular size Bundt pan.
Cut through batter to remove air bubbles.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: romanian stew
directions: Lay pork chops on bottom of casserole.
Put 4 tablespoons uncooked rice on each chop, 1 tablespoon chopped onion and 1 tablespoon green pepper on each chop.
Pour over 1 large can tomato puree; salt and pepper.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add warm water if necessary.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix warm macaroni and cheese until cheese is melted.
Then mix with all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese until softened.
Gradually stir in pineapple. Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in reserved nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, 1 1/3 cups of the instant puffs (dry), the egg, salt, pepper, onion, catsup and milk.
Spread in ungreased pie pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes.
Prepare remaining instant puffs as directed on package for 4 servings.
Top baked meat loaf with mashed potatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra.
(Be sure pods are small, leaving a short stem on each.)
Pack in hot clean jars.
Place 1 pepper, 1 clove garlic and onions in each jar.
Heat vinegar, water and salt to a boil. Pour hot liquid over okra and seal.
Let stand 8 weeks before using.
Makes 10 pints.

title: browned rice
directions: In electric skillet, saute pepper, onion and carrots (2 teaspoons shortening).
Lower heat.
Add rice and mix well.
May be served with beef, pork or chicken.
Two to 3 drops Kitchen Bouquet may be added to make rice brown.

title: chicken divine(serves 4)
directions: Place cut up chicken in the bottom of casserole dish and top with broccoli.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, water and mushrooms together.
Pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Goes well with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Coat with pancake mix (flour will work if you don't have mix in the cabinet).
Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown chops on both sides.
Remove chops and place in a shallow roasting pan.
Saute onions in remaining oil.
Mix condensed soup with water and pour in skillet.
When hot, pour over chops.
Spoon rice between chops and cover with soup mixture.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: anna and veronica's bread
directions: With your hands, mix the yeast with the water.
Mix the flour gradually into the water-yeast mixture. Let dough rise 1 hour, covered very well (clean towels, folded sheets).
Divide dough into 6 balls.
Keep dough balls covered while you are making more balls.
Set balls on clean sheet that is covering a table.
Let balls rest 10 mins.
Flatten dough into circles using your finger tips.
Work from around the outside, then down through the middle. Cover and let set 15 mins.
Bake at 500°.
Place on lower rack without pan.
Bake for 3 mins. until bottom browns, turn over and bake until brown on the bottom.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Line with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding over crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and other half of pudding.
End with another layer of crackers. Frost with chocolate icing.
Refrigerate and let set overnight. (I use prepared frosting.)

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries; stir gently to separate strawberries.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Spread evenly with sour cream.
Pour remaining mix on top.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields 12 servings.

title: oven steak dinner
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 1/2 hours.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans.
Spread evenly over pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Put butter and sugar into hot mashed potatoes; beat until dissolved.
Sift baking powder and flour together.
To the butter and sugar mixture, beat in 1 egg at a time, then add the milk and flavoring.
Add flour slowly until dough is easy to handle.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot fat.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: baked garlic appetizer(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Slice 1/4 inch off tops of garlic heads opposite root end.
Remove any loose outer papery skin. Place garlic cut side up in medium sized baking dish.
Arrange butter slices evenly over garlic.
Pour olive oil over evenly.
Add 2 cups broth to dish.
Arrange sun-dried tomatoes around garlic. Sprinkle fines herbs over the top.
Season with pepper.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes - until garlic and sun-dried tomatoes are tender, basting with broth every 15 minutes, adding more broth if necessary to maintain some sauce in pan.
Arrange goat cheese around garlic and continue to bake approximately 10 minutes - until cheese is almost melted.
Garnish with fresh basil. Serve with Italian bread.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. In a mixing bowl, combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots. Fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter and spread in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetables on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: midwest chops and pot bake
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup fried onions.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes.

title: squash deluxe
directions: Cut squash into
chunks
and
boil until tender; drain. Saute stuffing in margarine; set aside.
Combine chicken soup, sour cream, water chestnuts, onion, pimento and squash.	Using an 8-inch square Pyrex,
put
half
of
crumb	mixture
on the bottom, then all of
squash mixture and top with other half of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(two)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon and salt with electric mixer; add beaten eggs.
Sift in flour while mixing.
Pour equally into 2 raw pie shells. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; season to taste.
In separate bowl, mix soup, chopped chilies, onions and milk.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer uncooked tortillas, browned beef, grated cheese and soup mixture until all is used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together syrup, sugar, salt and peanuts.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 minutes more.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup mixture, blending well.
Microwave 1 minute more on High.
Remove and add baking soda; gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour into a sheet of aluminum foil.
Let cool 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: jean's cookies
directions: Mix egg, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add anything else you want (chocolate chips, coconut, nuts, raisins).
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Dip in beaten egg.
Dip in milk and cracker crumbs.
Coat well.
Brown in butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour grease (butter) over meat.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: german dinner
directions: Brown sausage; cook noodles.
Place layer of sauerkraut in bottom of Dutch oven, then layer of noodles, followed with layer of sausage.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 1 hour over low heat. Yields 4 servings.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Stir in liquids well.
Let get real cold and serve.
(Good for diabetics.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
together;
roll
in
small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until light brown.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Do not cook macaroni; mix it with rest of ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour before baking.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in 9 x 13-inch casserole or any casserole dish of equal capacity.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Will need a Bundt pan.

title: lemon love
directions: Spread over top of baked crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Add green pepper, garlic, onion, celery and oatmeal to ground chuck.
Work in eggs, milk, 1/4 can cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Shape and put in loaf pan.
Mix remaining soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce and spread on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender but not brown. Crush or blend can tomatoes.
Stir in the tomatoes and next 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Makes 4 quarts.
Serve over pasta.

title: sticky buns
directions: Break 1 loaf into 12 pieces; place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over dough.
Break second loaf into pieces and place on top.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Lightly grease top of loaf and turn onto plate.

title: mexican delight
directions: Simmer all ingredients 1/2 hour; add rice.
Continue to simmer until rice is covered.
Arrange on tray or Lazy Susan:
fresh chopped tomatoes, onions, avocado, lettuce and 2 cups grated Longhorn cheese.
Slightly crumble Fritos on plate.
Top with ground beef combo and favorite other toppings.
Top with lettuce, cheese and salsa.

title: marinated stuffed filet of beef
directions: Saut first 3 ingredients in 1 teaspoon hot vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 10 minutes or until liquid is evaporated; cool. Stir together soy sauce and next 5 ingredients. Make a 1-inch deep cut lengthwise down top of tenderloin. Spoon mushroom mixture into cut. Tie tenderloin with cotton string at 1-inch intervals. Place in large shallow dish. Pour soy sauce mixture over top of tenderloin; cover and chill 2 to 8 hours, turning occasionally. Remove tenderloin from marinade, reserving marinade. Place tenderloin on a lightly greased rack in a roasting pan. Add 1 cup water to roasting pan. Bring reserved marinade to a boil in a small saucepan over medium-high heat. Boil 1 minute. Bake tenderloin at 425° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a meat thermometer inserted in thickest portion registers 145° (medium-rare) to 160° (medium), basting occasionally with reserved marinade and covering with aluminum foil the last 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Place the lemonade, strawberries, sugar and rum in a blender. Fill the blender with ice cubes.
Blend until mixture is smooth. Pour daiquiris into glass; garnish each serving with a fresh, ripe strawberry.
Serves 6.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in blender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls and fry.
Put in spaghetti sauce and serve.

title: whipped lime jello
directions: Sprinkle cracker crumbs into bottom of a 9 x 11-inch container. Whip chilled milk.
Add sugar and ReaLemon.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and let cool.
Whip cooled Jell-O into whipped milk.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle more crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: parsley meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except bay leaves and catsup; stir well.
Shape into a loaf and place in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch two-piece loaf pan with drain holes in the bottom.
Arrange bay leaves on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Remove from pan and discard bay leaves; spread catsup over meat loaf.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet together, then combine with dry.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keeps up to 6 weeks in refrigerator covered tightly.
I use a Tupperware container in the refrigerator to keep some already baked and then put them in the microwave for 30 seconds on High to heat up for breakfast.

title: chili con carne
directions: In hot oil, brown turkey.
Add onions, peppers, tomato sauce, kidney beans, chili powder and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook slowly over a low heat for one hour.
Serve with hot Italian bread.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: By hand, mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add Wesson oil, eggs, flavorings and pineapple.
Add nuts and chopped bananas last.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° until done, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Add salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze juice out.
Add carrot, pepper and onion.
Make a syrup of vinegar, water and sugar.
Add mustard and celery seed.
Boil 1 minute. Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Put in containers and freeze.
This slaw can be refrozen several times.
Do not use blender.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Combine cereal and water (let stand until water is absorbed). Blend eggs and sugar.
Add syrup, butter, vanilla and salt; mix in cereal.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is puffed up across top of pie.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Add soup mix to sour cream; let stand 2 hours.
Place chicken in a roasting pan.
Pour sherry, water, salt, parsley flakes, pepper, basil and curry over chicken.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (less if boneless breasts).
Remove chicken.
Cool.
Strain liquid and reduce to 1 1/2 cups.
Add soup and let simmer.
Remove from heat and slowly add to sour cream. Cook rice as package directs.
Cut and pull chicken into bite size hunks; add to wild rice.
Butter a large casserole.
Put in rice and chicken.
Pour sauce over; mix well but lightly.
Heat at 300° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
If you make it beforehand, remove from refrigerator 1 1/2 hours before cooking.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Butter 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In large saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well. Spread half of mixture in pan.
Refrigerate.
Stir peanuts into remaining mixture.
Set aside.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins, sugar, water, cinnamon and salt in saucepan. Let simmer for 15 minutes until raisins are plump.

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine chopped orange slices, milk, coconut, pecans, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Bake in long dish until bubbly at 300°.
Then stir in confectioners sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper until firm.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: In 2-quart casserole, layer cucumbers and onions. Sprinkle with salt. Repeat layers and salt. Cover tightly and drain off liquid every hour for 3 hours. Combine water, vinegar and sugar. Cover vegetables with this mixture and cover tightly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecue style chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut off and discard wing tips.
Cut each wing at joint to make 2 sections.
Place the wing pieces in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Drain fat from baking pan.

title: southwestern-style burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine egg, chips, green pepper, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; mix well.
Shape into four 3/4-inch thick patties.
Grill on an uncovered grill.
Place patties directly over medium-hot coals; cook 15 to 18 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once.
Top each patty with avocado slices and cheese.
Grill 1 to 2 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
To serve, place 1 lettuce leaf on bottom half of bun.
Top with cooked patty and salsa.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Add juice and sugar.
Stir until all sugar is dissolved.
Pour into ice cream pail and freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine and enjoy at 200 calories for all of it.
No fat.

title: rumaki(makes about 15 appetizers)
directions: Cut each strip of bacon (cross).
Wrap each half around 1 piece of liver, chestnut and scallion.
Place in a small shallow pan. Combine soy sauce, ginger, turmeric, garlic and curry powder.
Pour over contents in pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Arrange on rack in broiler pan.
Place under a preheated hot broiler for 7 to 10 minutes.
Keep turning.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put in crock-pot.
Cover and cook 10 hours.

title: cream corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful into hot grease. Drain on paper towel.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and frozen strawberries; stir until strawberries are thawed and mixture begins to thicken.
Add pineapple and bananas to cooled mixture; mix thoroughly.
Pour 1/2 into oblong pan.
Refrigerate until set, the spread with sour cream.
Pour other half of Jell-O mixture on top; return to refrigerator to set until firm.

title: angel delight
directions: The intrigue starts with the flavors; a subtle snap of peppermint swirled with chocolate. More intrigue in the minty chocolate glaze. Be ready to share the recipe.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together and spread in cake pan and bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: dirt dessert(fills 8-inch plastic flowerpot)
directions: You will also need a flowerpot and garden shovel.

title: quick soup
directions: Combine in a kettle and cook until carrots and macaroni are done.
(I also add some onion.)

title: southern living's chicken and spinach enchiladas(mexican)
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven. Add salt and water to cover. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until tender. Remove chicken and let cool slightly. Bone chicken; dice and set aside.

title: broccoli and apple salad
directions: Mix all together and pour Sweet and Sour Dressing over to serve.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix dressing according to package directions.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: megan's casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add salt and pepper, green pepper and onion.
Cook about 25 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes. Pour in baking dish and top with cooked macaroni.
Place several slices of cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and half of the onion.
Drain.
Set aside.
Heat soup, sour cream, green chilies and remainder of onion thoroughly. Warm tortillas.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter over medium heat until clear.
Add zucchini and saute for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Saute for 10 more minutes or until zucchini is soft.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add grated cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(It can be reheated.)

title: swedish meat ball soup
directions: In a bowl, beat egg; add 1/3 c. cream, bread crumbs, onion and 1 tsp. salt.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into 1/2 in. balls. In a dutch oven or soup kettle, brown meatballs in butter, half at a time. Remove from pan; set aside.
Drain fat.
To pan, add flour, bouillon, pepper, garlic salt and remaining salt; stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in water and bring to a boil, stirring often.
Add potatoes and meat balls.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.
Stir in the peas and remaining cream; heat through.

title: plantation fudge cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and lightly flour two 9-inch cake pans.
Combine the butter, sugar, and melted chocolate in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
In medium bowl, combine the flour, salt, and baking soda. Stir to mix.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk, starting and ending with the flour mixture.
Divide the batter evenly between the prepared pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center of layers comes out clean.
Remove from pans immediately and cool on a rack.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 6 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in reserved juice.
Add butter, cheese and pineapple.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add Ritz crackers on top and reduce oven to 250°.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Add Cool Whip to top and chill.
Sprinkle crushed nuts on top.

title: tiny cream cheese biscuits
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed with electric mixer 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add flour, beating at a low speed just until blended.
Spoon dough into ungreased miniature muffin pans, filling full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve immediately.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 dozen.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions and beat in the cream cheese.
Add dry Jello powder, stirring until dissolved, then add pineapple and oranges.
Chill.

title: popsicles
directions: Boil water.
Dissolve
jello, sugar and Kool-Aid in hot water. Stir well,
then add cold water.
Put mixture in small Dixie cups or	some other small container.
When partly frozen put in popsicle sticks.

title: english muffins in a loaf
directions: *Measure flour by spooning flour lightly into cup.

title: temptations
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape into 36 (1-inch) balls.
Place in lightly greased small muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Dough will rise during baking.
Remove from oven.
Press peanut butter cup into each hot crust.
Cool completely.
Remove from pan. Makes 3 dozen.

title: beef and rice stroganoff
directions: Brown beef until crumbly;
drain.
Add tomatoes, broth, mushrooms, onion, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and rice.
Stir
well.
Simmer
until
rice
is tender, about 20 minutes.
Serve in bowls.
Top each serving with sour cream.

title: easy fettuccine
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in skillet on low heat until golden brown.
Stir in process cheese spread, milk and Parmesan cheese until melted.
Add fettuccine; mix lightly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour and sugar and set aside.
Mix butter, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar mixture and mix.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well, then pour into a large greased sheet cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in the refrigerator for several hours.
Remove from refrigerator, shape into a ball and roll in a mixture of 1/4 cup chopped walnuts, 3 tablespoons parsley and 2 cups diced, cooked bacon.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Mix well and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Use the egg whites for meringue.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan in boiling water, cook broccoli, cauliflowerets and carrots 3 minutes; drain.
In shallow baking dish, arrange cooked vegetables, tomatoes and chicken.
In cup, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and chicken. Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 3 cups.

title: mom's yeast rolls(no-knead refrigerator rolls)
directions: Stir together sugar and yeast until liquid.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add butter in small bits.
Add alternately milk and flour. Add salt and beat well.
Put in a cool place overnight, such as the refrigerator.
The next day, knead and roll out; divide into thirds.
Roll each third into a large circle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 16 sections and roll each section into a crescent, starting at large end.
Let rise until light.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients in the order given in a large bowl.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted into center of pie filling comes out clean.

title: jamaican pork chops
directions: Add all the spices together and place in a small glass bowl. Add green onions, minced garlic, vegetable oil and lemon juice. Stir well.
Put chops in a large Ziploc bag.
Pour marinade over. Close and shake.
Marinate for 2 hours or overnight for better flavor.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook contents of rice and seasoning packets according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk and chicken broth. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken and cooked rice.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: boiled custard(not boiled)
directions: Mix ingredients, cool in refrigerator 35 minutes.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip and a little nutmeg on top of custard.

title: crunchy fish dilly
directions: Soak fish fillets in lemon juice and water.
In a large plastic bag, combine cracker crumbs with salt, lemon peel, dill and pepper.
Drain fish and pat dry.
Dip in beaten egg and then in cracker crumb mixture.
Fry in 1/4 to 1/2-inch hot oil for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: butterscotch goodies
directions: In a large bowl, melt in microwave the chips and peanut butter for 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave until melted.
Stir well.
Mix in cereal until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Put in freezer until solid.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meaty macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook
macaroni	according
to package directions; drain. Brown beef, onion and celery in butter, in large skillet; drain off excess
fat.
Stir	in
tomato
sauce or tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Combine with macaroni and pour into 2 quart casserole. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: beth page's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a large baking dish.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in blender container. Cover and process at blend speed until perfectly smooth.
Fill well-greased muffin tins, custard cups, or popover pans half full. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes longer.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a jar.
Mix well.
Place salad in a large bowl.
Just before serving, add dressing. Garnish with bacon bits and eggs.

title: potatoes 'n sour cream dressing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Layer potatoes in casserole dish and spread sour cream mixture over top.
I make three layers and add sour cream mixture on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: double delicious halloween bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over bottom of pan.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs and oil.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and oats.
Mix and drop by teaspoon onto a tray of powdered sugar.
Roll thoroughly.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° not more than 7 to 8 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions.
Break up bread and croutons.
Pour juice over.
Add celery and onions.
Add little bit of sage.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: Grease a deep pie dish, bottom and sides.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, butter, egg,	pudding
and
milk. Beat and pour into pie dish.
Drain peaches	real well reserving peach juice.
Arrange
peaches
on
top
of batter.
Beat cream cheese, sugar
and	3
tablespoons peach juice.
Spread over peaches and batter
and
leave	1
inch around edge, not covered.
(The batter
will
raise
to
make crust.) Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar on top.
Bake	at
350° for 35 minutes.
Chill overnight for best results before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, crab, onion juice, almonds and milk.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Heat at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: tarheel pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare pastry for 8-inch (1-crust) pie. Combine eggs, molasses, syrup, coffee, melted butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine pecans and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until firm.

title: cheese and spinach bake
directions: Cook the spinach, scallions and nutmeg in a small amount of water (15 minutes). Drain well. Spread the mixture on bottom of a small baking dish. Top with the mixture of cheese and oregano. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Jell-O pudding and milk.
Beat well.
Add cream cheese and
sour cream; blend them.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put layer of vanilla wafers and bananas; add 1/2 of mixture.
Then layer vanilla wafers and bananas and rest of mixture.
Top with other half of Cool Whip.

title: american lasagna(pierogies)
directions: In frypan, saute onions in oleo.
Boil lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Boil potatoes and mash them (don't add milk).
Add American cheese and 1/4 of the onions.
Mix well.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350°.
This
is the moist cake and if you leave it out overnight, it will still be fresh and moist.

title: tropical sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and cut into large pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with pecans and marshmallows.
Set aside.
Mix sugars, butter, cinnamon and juice from orange sections in saucepan.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Add orange sections and spread over potatoes.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Blend in flour. Stir in walnuts. Drop in spoonfuls and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: chile rellenos puff
directions: Rinse chiles; pat dry with paper towel.
Slit lengthwise; carefully remove any seeds found inside.
Cut Monterey Jack cheese into 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips; place inside chile peppers.
Place chiles side by side in greased baking dish (8 cup size).
Beat eggs until foamy; beat in milk, flour and baking powder until smooth.
Pour over chiles.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top. Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 minutes until set in the middle. Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with salsa.

title: 1930's leftover mashed potato cakes
directions: Mashed potatoes must be shaped into patties after the meal before refrigerating.

title: cheesy noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place unopened can of Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk in a pan.
Cover with at least an inch of water.
Turn oven on high until water boils.
Turn oven down just enough to keep the water boiling.
Boil for three hours.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done; drain.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream. Stir in pickles, onion, celery seed, salt and pepper. Add mustard, red wine vinegar and eggs. Mix thoroughly.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken in casserole.
Mix all ingredients (except pineapple) together.
Spread over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and place pineapple rings on top and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: pasta and vegetable toss
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion, garlic and Italian seasoning in oil until tender.
Add water, bouillon and vegetables. Cover and let simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until tender crisp. Toss with hot fettucine.
Makes 4 servings.

title: merry meringues
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in a small bowl with electric mixer on high speed for 5 minutes or until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tsp. at a time, beating on high speed until soft peeks form.
Drop tablespoonfuls of the egg white mixture onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Sprinkle each meringue lightly with dry gelatin powders.
Bake at 225 degrees for 50 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Prop oven door open slightly and let meringues stand in the oven for about 1 hour or until completely cooled.
Store meringues in a tightly covered container at room temperature.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine cream-style corn and 1/2 cup milk or whole kernel corn and 3/4 cup milk.
Add crumbs, onion, green pepper and seasonings. Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bug mountain cake
directions: Mix cake according to box.
Bake one cake in a 13 x 9 pan, cook the other cake in a 1 liter bowl.
Place the 13 x 9 on dish. then place the bowl shaped cake on top.
Heat icing in microwave for about 30 seconds, stir well and pour over the cake.
Spread icing over uncovered areas.
Then take cookie mix and sprinkle over the entire cake.
Place plastic bugs, and snakes all over.
(The cookie sprinkles are found in the ice cream topping section at the grocery store.)

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then stir in oil and egg.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: jam and cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese, walnuts, onion and mayonnaise.
You may need a little more mayonnaise to hold first three ingredients together.

title: liver pate
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, blending thoroughly.
Then chill for at least 1 hour.
Then form mixture into a ball.
Take rye bread and hollow out in the center.
Drop in liver pate ball. Serve.

title: alex's favorite cookies
directions: Combine all together. Roll into balls and press with fork. Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Empty peaches into 9 x 13 baking pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over and press down firmly. Cut butter into small pieces and place on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: frozen slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Cool; add water and sugar to juices and freeze.
Fill glass 1/4 to 1/2 full.
Finish filling with 7-Up or Sprite.
Makes cool summer drink.

title: peach cooler
directions: Blend all ingredients, except 7-Up, until smooth.
Fill glasses 1/2 full with blended mixture.
Fill glasses with 7-Up and stir gently.

title: rosemary carrots
directions: Place carrots in 2-quart casserole.
In small bowl or 2-cup measure, combine bouillon, water, sugar and seasonings.
Pour over carrots.
Toss to coat; cover.
Microwave at High 5 to 8 minutes or until fork-tender, stirring once after half the cooking time.

title: "stuffed eggs"
directions: Cut eggs in halves; slip out yolks.
Mash with fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refill whites with yolk mixture.
Let cool and serve.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken and steamed vegetables
directions: Combine lemon juice, garlic and parsley in bowl.
Mix well. Combine chicken and vegetables in large bowl.
Pour lemon juice mixture over chicken.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Heat oil in medium-sized skillet.
Add chicken; cook for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables with lemon juice and cook until tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sue's oyster stew
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots (steaming them is best, using a microwave to do this is the fastest way).
Saute onions and celery in butter in pan.
Strain potatoes and carrots and add to pan. Add milk and ground pepper.
Heat to boiling point.
Add oysters. (Note:
Oysters cook very quickly, so do not add them until you are ready to serve or turn the burner off after you add them.)

title: cherry cobbler pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk; bake on baking sheet until light brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove crust from oven.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add eggs, fruit cocktail, pecans, coconut and pineapple.
Put layer of vanilla wafers, then layer of mixture.
Leave layer of wafers on top.
Put in icebox; let get cold.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour uncooked Minute rice over butter.
Mix the 2 soups with the milk and pour over rice.
Press chicken into the mixture.
Cover with foil and seal tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek!

title: old fashion recipe(for punch bowl or by the drink)
directions: Mix and allow to stand overnight, if possible.
Serve over crushed ice.
Garnish with lemon slices, orange slices and cherries.
(Wedges of pineapple in punch bowl over block of ice.) Can mix and use to serve single servings.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and salt together; then add to butter mixture.
Add nuts.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown at 350°.
Cool; then roll into confectioners sugar.

title: main dish spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain well.
Remove meat from skillet and set aside.
In same skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Saute onion and green pepper in reserved drippings until crisp-tender.
Stir in ground beef, crumbled bacon and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 5.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw the dough 6 to 8 hours.
Combine loaves; roll out to 1/4-inch thickness (18 x 12-inch).
Spread 2 beaten eggs on dough (not edges).
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and parsley.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over this and lay pepperoni slices on top.
Start rolling longest side away from you.
Roll and push pepperoni in at the same time.
Bring edge to top and pinch ends and seam.
Place on pan, seam side down.
Spread beaten egg on top and sprinkle with poppy or sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Can be made as 2 separate loaves or cut dough in half before baking.

title: carrot nut scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly butter a 10-inch diameter circle in the center of a baking sheet.
In a large bowl stir together the flour, wheat germ, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Cut butter into 1/2 inch cubes and distribute them over the flour mixture.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion, cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
In a small bowl stir together the yogurt, egg and vanilla.
Add the yogurt mixture to the flour mixture and stir to combine.
Stir in the carrots, raisins and pecans.
The dough will be sticky.
Spread the dough into an 8 1/2-inch diameter circle in the center of the prepared baking sheet.
With a serrated knife, cut into 8 wedges.
Bake for 19 to 21 minutes or until the top is lightly browned and a toothpick inserted into the center of a scone comes out clean.
Remove the baking sheet to a wire rack and cool for 5 minutes.
With a spatula, transfer scones to the wire rack to cool.
Serve warm or cool completely and store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Let them reach room temperature or warm slightly before servings.
Makes 8 scones.

title: coconut orange cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the sugar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add mandarin oranges and egg;
beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 8 inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack for 15 minutes.

title: easy boiled custard
directions: Add pudding mix, sugar and vanilla to milk; stir until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until very, very cold.

title: chicken salad deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Add celery, grapes, coconut, pineapple and chicken.
Mix together the Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Add to salad and blend well.
Refrigerate.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix together in food processor or with mixer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: honey apple tea
directions: In a 2-quart pot, brew tea bags in boiling water.
Remove tea bags.
Add honey and apple juice.
Simmer until hot.
Ladle into cups and garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into balls.
Chill.
Melt Wiltons wafers and dip balls.
Then refrigerate.

title: anchovies in dough
directions: Thaw dough and let rise.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Take piece of dough and roll out flat.
Semi-drain anchovy.
Place anchovy fillets in center.
Roll back up into a ball.
Seal tightly.
Fry in hot oil on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: crab casserole
directions: This recipe is adapted from one by Paul Prudhomme.
The amount of pepper is half of what he suggests.
You may want to reduce it even more since most people think that even this is too spicy!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Add 1 can cream-style corn.
Mix and if dryer than desired, add buttermilk.
Stir in meat mixture and bake to a golden brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover the cucumbers, onions and salt with water; let stand overnight, then drain.
Put all ingredients except cucumbers and onions in pan and boil.
Add cucumbers and onions; boil again. Pack in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 12 pints.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Brown burger and onion.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt. Add 1 1/4 cups milk and cream cheese; cook and stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Add a moderate amount of hot mixture to egg; return to hot mixture in skillet.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in chopped, cooked broccoli; set aside.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with half of pastry.
Spoon in hot mixture.
Cut or shred Jack cheese and put in hot mixture.
Put on top pie crust, seal and make steam vents with a fork.
Brush top of pie with milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: punch
directions: Add water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze overnight.
Take out 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale to make more.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger. Add sauce, water, salt and pepper; simmer. Combine eggs and cheeses, reserving 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese. Stuff mixture into uncooked shells; arrange single layer in 9 x 12-inch pan. Completely cover with sauce. Add 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese on top. Cover and bake at 325° about 1 hour, until noodles are soft.

title: low calorie microwave baked apples
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour soda over apples.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes before serving.

title: vinegar and cold water pickles
directions: Mix the pickling mixture cold. Pour over cucumbers and finish filling jar with cold water. Seal tight for 4 weeks or more.

title: elsewood's marinade for brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over brisket in Pyrex.
Marinate overnight.
Turn several times.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cube in casserole dish.
Cube cheese over potatoes.
Add onion and pimento.
Cube bread on top. Melt butter; pour on top of bread cubes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 15 minutes until cheese melts at 350°.

title: isabel's delight
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Cover with unsalted saltines (4 across, 7 to 9 down).
Melt 1/2 cup butter and mix with 1 cup sugar.
Stir continuously while boiling for 3 minutes.
Pour over saltines.
Then pour 12 ounces chocolate bits on top.
Put in oven for 2 minutes at 350°.
When chocolate is melted, spread over crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until hard, break into pieces.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large pan.
Arrange bacon slices across top.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in blender; do in 3 batches. Mix blended and dry ingredients. Add chopped nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until an inserted toothpick comes out clean. Delicious!

title: kugel(noodle casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan and remove from oven.
Cook the egg noodles until done and drain well. Add sour cream, well-beaten eggs, cottage cheese, salt and sugar to the noodles.
Pour the mixture into the pan with the margarine and sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of rice and dot with butter.
Lay chicken pieces over top of rice and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix chicken soup, chicken broth and the can of water together and pour over top of rice and chicken.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: In large bowl, combine potatoes, eggs and pickle.
Stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing, pickle juice, salt, pepper, celery seed and garlic salt.
Gently fold mayonnaise mixture into potato mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with additional egg slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Preheat
oven
at
Mix
yellow of eggs in mixing bowl; pour in sugar and mix until dissolved.
Add butter; beat until creamy.
Add flour, half and half cream, milk and water. Add juice squeezed from lemons; pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Form into a loaf.
Place in pan and top with bacon slices. Pour extra cup of tomato juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: nana's country style chicken
directions: This charcoal broiled steak is very delicious and very famous in Korea.
It can be prepared from prime rib, sirloin, tip round or chuck steak.
The chuck has superior flavor and is quite tender when properly cut into narrow strips.
Also, it is the most economical.
If using sirloin, you may wish to leave the steak whole.
Top round steak may be either cut into serving size pieces or cut into the narrow strips in the same manner as the chuck.
I prefer to use the top round steak cut into the narrow strips, as this is how the dish is served in Korea.

title: glazed pork loin with garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Season pork loin with salt and pepper and place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast in center of oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours (about 25 to 30 minutes per pound), or until meat thermometer inserted in center of loin registers 165 degrees.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand overnight to raise.
In the morning, thin the batter with warm water and add a pinch of soda. Bake on greased griddle.
Cakes are ready to turn when they are filled with little bubbles.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly. Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, building up slight edges.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain and place in pot.
Add tomatoes, puree and garlic and simmer 10 minutes.
Add chili powder, cumin, oregano and Tabasco.
Simmer 10 minutes and taste.
Add salt and pepper as needed.
Can also sprinkle small amount (about 1/2 teaspoon) of sugar if too acidy. Simmer 20 minutes, then add beans and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
