Serve in bowl over rice or plain. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: my special pimento cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: country chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown in oil in heavy skillet.
Remove from pan.
In same pan, saute lightly the onions, green pepper and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni, and simmer 10 minutes.

title: layered enchilada dinner
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all together except cheese.
Layer the mixture and cheese between 6 lightly buttered tortillas. Alternate tortilla, meat and cheese.
Save 1/2 cup cheese for top. Add 2/3 cup water around sides.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage hot dish
directions: Brown the ground beef. Add the salt, pepper, onion and green pepper. Saute with the meat.
Place in greased casserole dish. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Hollow out loaf of bread. Place mix in bread.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add flour. Put salt, baking soda and baking powder into mixture; mix well. Add vanilla and zucchini by folding in.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix pineapple, rhubarb, and sugar. then let it set for 1 1/2 hours.
Bring to a boil and boil for 15 minutes.
Stir in a 3 oz. package of strawberry jello.
Put into hot jars and seal.
Very good!

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Form cakes.
Do not pack firmly.
Roll crackers into fine crumbs and pat lightly on crab cakes.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Blend dry mix, eggs, oil and dry pudding mix together. Add the 7-Up and beat for 4 minutes. Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: aunt rosie's raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water for 10 minutes.
(Use saucepan big enough to mix cake in.)
Take off fire.
Add oleo that has been cut in fourths.
When cold, put in beaten egg and vanilla.
Then add sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Put in pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until it tests done in center. Nuts may be added.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with favorite icing.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
While browning, chop very fine the onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add soup; heat.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice until done.
Add chicken, soup, lemon juice, butter, grated cheese, mayo and chicken broth.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Top with Topping.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Blend eggs and oil with wire whip.
Add soda, salt, baking powder and sugar and mix well with whip.
Add alternately flour and buttermilk.
Beat well with wire whip.
Cook on griddle over medium heat until bubbles begin to pop and turn to bake other side.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook meat until almost done.
Add carrots and onions; cook a little while (30 minutes), then add potatoes and cook until done. May also make a little brown gravy and add, if desired.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat egg and add with cheese; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk to the first mixture.
Turn into a greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese, chips and almonds.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: honey barbecue marinated chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken on one side.
Mix rest of ingredients and add chicken.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Barbecue on low until chicken is cooked.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook wild rice as directed.
Mix ingredients together in large casserole (can be frozen or refrigerated and cooked later).
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until leaves are tender enough to roll.
Let cabbage cool to touch.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, water and eggs together.
Add rice after it has cooled off.
Put combined ingredients in cabbage leaves, folding the leaves over filling.
Use leftover cabbage to line bottom of pot to prevent burning.
Put stuffed cabbage in pot, adding enough water to steam (1 1/2 cups).
Add margarine on top. Steam 45 minutes.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add flour mixture, alternately with the milk to the sugar and shortening.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately when done, dip in 1/2 cup melted butter and roll in 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Bring to boiling point. Beat eggs.
Gradually add syrup mixture.
Add nuts, salt and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine ingredients with
1 (8 ounce) sour cream.
Heat 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sunday chicken supper
directions: In 5 quart slow-cooker, layer first 7 ingredients.
In a bowl mix the rest and pour on top.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook on low 6 - 9 hours.
Good and healthy.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Sprinkle on cake batter, reserving a small amount for top of cake.
Pour remaining batter into pan and top with remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Blend together well; chill or put into punch bowl containing block ice.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Combine crackers and nuts in a greased shallow baking pan.
In a saucepan, bring butter, sugar and corn syrup to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: teriyaki marinade(for london broil)
directions: Brown 2 tablespoons sesame seed in 1/2 cup salad oil.
Let cool.
In blender, mix the soy sauce, sugar, ginger, garlic salt and sesame seed; mix well.
Pour over meat.
Puncture steak with fork on all sides.
Let stand in marinade mixture 4 hours.
Grill or broil steak 7 minutes on each side.
Slice steak on a slant very thin across the grain.

title: cocktail quiche
directions: Broil fish fillet about five minutes 2 to 3 inches from the flame.
Pierce with a fork at 1-inch intervals.
Spread with butter or ?
Season with Cajun seasoning or ?
Return to broiler for five minutes or until done.
Garnish with lemon, parsley, dill and/or ? Serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Add alternately the flour and milk; mix well.
Stir in flavoring and mix until blended.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° (preheat) for 70 to 90 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: In a bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower, green peas, green onions, bacon, eggs and cheese.
Spread with topping as though icing a cake.
Let set overnight; toss before serving.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Thaw lemonade and combine with Cool Whip and milk until smooth and creamy.
Pour into pie crust and chill for 1/2 hour.

title: judy's homemade soup
directions: Put olive oil in bottom of soup pot.
Add hamburger, bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Brown together.
Add all seasonings.
Add all vegetables and 2 cups water.
In separate bowl, mix soups and remaining water with wire whisk until well blended.
Add to soup pot.
Stir thoroughly. (You may add any other veggies, (raw, canned, frozen, or left-over) as desired at this time.) If using potatoes, add at this time as well.
If using rice or pasta, simmer soup 30 minutes then add.
Continue cooking for an additional 30 minutes.
Add water to make soup desired consistancy.

title: farmer style fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, place the Milnot, marshmallow cream and sugar.
Mix and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 10 full minutes.
Add this hot mixture to the chip mixture, stirring well, until all the chips have melted.
Pour into buttered pan and place in refrigerator until hard, at least 3 hours. Cut into squares.

title: shipwreck
directions: Cook together hamburger and salt.
Add onion and celery and cook.
Wash off kidney bean juice and add.
Butter pan. Alternate hamburger mixture with potatoes.
Pour 1 can tomato soup on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In pan, combine brown sugar and 1/2 stick margarine; melt. Spread on bottom of 9-inch round cake pan.
Arrange peaches on top in circles.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon. In large bowl, beat remaining margarine and sugar until creamy. Beat in egg yolks.
Mix in flour mixture with milk and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Spread over peaches and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn onto plate.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, 1 can crushed pineapple with juice and 1 can mandarin oranges with juice.
Mix well and pour into 3 round cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and ice, then refrigerate.

title: chicken ranchero
directions: In 8 x 10-inch lightly oiled baking dish, put crunched Doritos.
Tear chicken into small pieces and place on top of Doritos.

Mix and heat Ro-Tel tomatoes and both soups in pan until hot (use juice of tomatoes and just enough water where the sauce is a medium texture; you don't want it too thick or too thin). Pour this over your chicken.
Add onion and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini medley
directions: Brown bacon in large skillet and remove.
Saute zucchini, onion and green pepper in bacon grease until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, corn and lima beans.
Cover until all vegetables are tender.
Remove lid; crumble bacon.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: cheese filled meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese; mix well. Divide meat into thirds. Put 1/3 meat in bottom of loaf pan. Cover with half the cheese. Repeat layers, ending with meat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: philly cream cheese apricot cookies
directions: Combine margarine, granulated sugar and cream cheese; mixing until well blended.
Blend in eggs, juice and rind.
Add combined flour and baking powder; mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape level tablespoonful of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly, indent centers; fill with preserves.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 7 dozen.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix together rhubarb and white sugar.
Place in a well greased 9 X 9 inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well until crumbly.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until rhubarb is tender and topping is golden brown. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam spray.
In the casserole dish, mix pineapple, sugar, egg and flour.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Saute bread cubes in butter until lightly browned and place on top of pineapple mix.
Lower oven heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: fruited raisin muffins
directions: Combine bran, yogurt, milk, butter and egg product; let stand for 5 minutes.
In bowl, blend flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon; stir in bran mixture just until blended.
Stir in cranberries and raisins.
Spoon batter into 9 greased 3-inch muffin pan cups.*
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm. *Twelve greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups may be substituted. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: bohemian nut roll
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over yeast.
Let stand 10 minutes for yeast to soften and form.
In large bowl, mix flour and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in egg yolks and yeast mixture; mix until a smooth ball is formed.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with peas.
Seal salad with mayonnaise.
Season mayonnaise with Lawry's seasoning.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss prior to serving.

title: green beans vinaigrette
directions: Place water, green beans and onion in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover tightly and microwave on High for 10 to 14 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes until beans are tender.
Drain.
Shake remaining ingredients in tightly covered container.
Toss with beans.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Wash peas, cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain and put peas and all ingredients into a large pot.
Cover with water and put lid on pot.
Bring slowly to a boil and simmer until tender. Cooked rice may be added to the peas before serving.

title: nuts, bolts and screws
directions: Melt butter in large roaster.
Pour in all cereals, nuts, pretzels and seasonings.
Set in oven at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In saucepan, combine pie filling with sugar, pineapple and juice, cornstarch and food coloring.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Allow to cool.
Add bananas and pecans. Pour into two baked pie shells and top with whipped topping. Chill.

title: *honey puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make a soft dough.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve hot topped with powdered sugar.

title: corn en casserole
directions: Brown meat and mix together with all ingredients.
Bake in a slow oven.

title: sausage cheese ball
directions: Fry sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly and browned. Combine sausage, cheese, pepper and biscuit mix; add water.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lard pie crust
directions: Combine flour, lard (softened) and water.
Mix until thick. Knead to desired consistency.
Makes 6 crusts.
Roll dough out and place in pan.

title: southern fried squirrel
directions: Boil squirrel until tender.
Remove from water, pat dry. Season and coat with flour.
Place into hot oil and cook until brown.
If desired, make brown gravy.

title: crock-pot chicken with orange sauce
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onion together until partially done. Mix the remaining ingredients together and cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly, because it burns easily.

title: luscious apricot squares
directions: Cover apricots with water and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain and chop.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together butter, sugar and 1 cup flour until crumbly.
Press mixture into bottom of prepared pan and bake 25 minutes.

title: calico slaw
directions: Cook peas and carrots as directed.
Drain and chill.
Mix together other ingredients and toss with chilled vegetables. Makes 8 servings.

title: fabulous cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.
At high speed, beat soft cream cheese with cottage cheese until creamy and well combined.
Gradually beat in sugar, then beat in eggs.
At low speed, beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add melted butter and sour cream; beat just until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around edges.
Turn off oven.
Let cake stand in oven 2 hours.
Remove. Let cool completely.
Refrigerate until well chilled, several hours.
To serve, run spatula around side of cheesecake to loosen. Remove spring-form and leave bottom.
Add fresh fruit.

title: apple coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, apples and carrots. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour the mayonnaise mixture over the cabbage mixture; toss well. Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: orange slice nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat in milk alternately with flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 3 1/2 hours at 250°.
Remove from oven.
Let stand until slightly cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and chop apples into smaller than bite size pieces.
Peel and section, then chop oranges the same as the apples.
Cut bananas in half lengthwise, then cut into pieces.
Add orange juice, nuts, cherries and cherry juice.
This will not keep over 2 days, but will not last any longer either.
You can use any kind of fruit in this, coconut, pineapple, etc.
Very good!

title: jam cake
directions: Combine soda and baking powder with milk and stir until mixed well.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and mix again.
Cook at 325° to 350° until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: ratatouille supreme
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil; saute eggplant and zucchini for 8 minutes.
Add the peppers and onion and simmer uncovered for another 6 minutes.
Add garlic and simmer 2 minutes.
Add wine, tomatoes, herbs, salt, pepper and black olives and cook covered in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until eggplant is tender.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: angel food apricot nectar cake
directions: Tear (or cube) angel food cake and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking
dish.
Heat (low boil) next 3 ingredients in a large saucepan until thick (like corn syrup).
Pour over the pieces of angel
food
cake
and
let cool.
Refrigerate. When ready to serve, top each serving with Cool Whip and garnish as desired (chocolate chips, cherries, strawberries, etc.).

title: italian chicken on the grill
directions: Soak chicken in Italian dressing for several hours (better if overnight) and grill until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a well-greased and floured skillet.
Sprinkle in cheese (make sure none of the cheese touches the edge of the pan), then pour in rest of batter.
Cook at 375° until golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add the other 4 ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (do not grease or flour).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done at 350°. Serves 12 to 15.

title: spiced sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pierce potatoes with a fork; arrange in a circle on paper towels in microwave oven.
Microwave at HIGH 16 minutes or until tender, rearranging potatoes after 8 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp into a large bowl.
Discard skins.
Add sugar and next 5 ingredients (sugar through nutmeg), and beat with a mixer at low speed until combined.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
8 servings. (serving size:

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour batter into greased tube pan.
Add filling, then rest of cake mixture.

title: pickled beets(sweet)
directions: Cook beets for about 30 minutes and peel.
Mix vinegar mixture in large pot and add beets.
Boil for 5 minutes and can.

title: chicken cheese sandwich
directions: Grind all ingredients except for mayonnaise and buns.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Spread on buns.
Wrap in foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar and grated rind.
Add cold water and beaten egg yolks.
Add milk, juice and butter.
Beat egg whites stiff and lightly fold into batter.
Place into buttered 8-inch square baking dish and place in pan of hot water.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: chicken strata
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until moist.
Put in pan, let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Mix together eggs, milk and soup. Pour over first mixture.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini squash and egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake uncovered at 300° for approximately 40 minutes or until brown.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil margarine, syrup and sugar 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add to syrup mixture 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn and nuts in large roasting pan; mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (ovens may vary), stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in covered container.

title: company pie
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Then add other ingredients.
Use your choice of fruit.
Pour into 2 pie shells.

title: make ahead mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Mash potatoes, gradually stirring in salad dressing, cream cheese, onion powder, salt and pepper until light and fluffy.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead dough on board.
Place in bowl; chill.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix together drained corn, pimentos, celery, onion, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Spread Cheddar cheese on top.
Toss cracker crumbs with melted margarine until coated, then spread on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, place cherry pie filling.
Spoon pineapple with juice over filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over this. Slice margarine and cover cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream margarine, beat in rest of ingredients except pecans. Beat mixture well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Double recipe for cookie sheet.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Can add a little bourbon, not over 1/4 cup for double recipe.

title: maple cream frosting
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually blend in Marshmallow Creme and syrup.
Spread on cake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook, drain and crumble sausage and beef. Mix first five ingredients together. Add hot pepper. Pour 1/2 of mixture in heated iron skillet. Sprinkle sausage and ground beef mixture over corn bread mixture, Sprinkle grated cheese on top of beef mixture, then corn and chopped onions. Spread remainder of cornbread over top and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat together on high speed the shortening, butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar until thoroughly combined, about 5 minutes.
Then beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat in vanilla and lemon juice.
In a bowl, stir together baking soda, salt, cinnamon, oats and flour.
Beat dry ingredients into the creamed mixture until well combined; mix in chocolate pieces and nuts.
For each cookie, drop approximately 1/4 cup dough on lightly greased baking sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: bean salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in a bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Broil wings until golden brown.
Removing tray from oven, put wings in large bowl with cover.
In small saucepan, put butter, garlic, vinegar, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Cook on medium heat until boiling.
Pour over the wings and cover.
Shake until wings are well covered with sauce.
Serve with celery, Blue cheese and fries.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Seed and chop peppers.
Blend peppers and 1/2 cup vinegar in blender. Add sugar and remainder of vinegar. Bring to a boil. When you cannot stir down the boil, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Skim, then add Certo and coloring.
Stir until liquid starts to thicken. Pour into sterilized jars.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Good on pork, chicken and beef.

title: no fat chocolate cake
directions: Heat milk until barely simmering.
Remove from heat and whisk in cocoa until thickened and smooth.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes, then add applesauce and vanilla.
Mix flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until thick and foamy.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour.
Stir just until blended.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Pour in prepared pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs well; add cornstarch.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, pepper and corn.
Pour in a greased 4-quart baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend the Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together; then put all the other ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and set overnight in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: brisslets
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Alternately add flour and cream.
Chilling the dough overnight is best.
Make dough in balls, 3/4-inch in diameter.
Bake in iron.
Electric irons can be purchased.
If using an electric iron, use 1 cup eggs and 5 1/3 cups flour (sift before measuring).
Then add sugar, butter, cream and vanilla as in original recipe.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add spices to flour and mix all together.
Add vanilla, nuts and thinly sliced apples; stir. Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: tuna or salmon dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Stir in soup and milk.
Gently stir in tuna (or salmon).
Heat to serving temperature.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Brown onion, garlic, okra and peppers in oil.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook over moderate heat until okra is tender and mixture thickens.
Add a little chopped parsley before serving, if desired.

title: rhonda's easy brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in big pot and simmer about 30 minutes. Great to freeze.

title: banananana nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients. With pastry blender, cut in margarine.
With fork, stir in bananas and eggs. Stir in nuts.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: cheesy tamale chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch.
Layer chicken, onion, chilies, cheese and corn in dish. Beat Bisquick milk, salt and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites in large bowl until stiff; fold in egg yolk mixture.
Pour over corn.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Lightly grease pan and place chicken.
Cover with slices of Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and wine; spoon over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle 1 cup stuffing on top and drizzle melted butter.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mexican seven layer dip
directions: Mix refried beans and avocado dressing together.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed in 5 x 8-inch pan.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix in chili con catne.
After a good mixture, add chili powder and hot sauce; then mix.
Add chili beans and tomato juice.
Heat until warm.
Add spaghetti, broken in thirds, and cook for 40 minutes.

title: milky way peas
directions: Heat milk.
Add frozen peas and stir until peas and milk are well mixed.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter and honey and serve.
Serves 6.

title: french toast
directions: Break eggs into large, flat bottomed bowl or soup plate.
Add milk; beat with egg beater.
Dip bread in egg mixture; let soak. Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Cover bottom with the butter.
Place soaked bread in skillet; cook until side of bread is browned.
Do same with other side.
Remove from skillet. Makes 4.

title: dilly cauliflower au gratin
directions: Steam cauliflower until done.
Cut into small pieces and place in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Blend margarine with flour, milk, cheese and seasonings.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over cauliflower.
Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese balls
directions: Set cheese out for 1 hour to soften.
Mix all ingredients well, setting aside 1/4 cup of nuts.
Divide mix into 2 parts and roll each into a large ball.
Roll in reserved nuts.
Serve with crackers.
This recipe may also be frozen.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into cakes. Fry.
Very good!

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place broccoli and broth in saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer about 8 minutes until broccoli is tender.

title: zippy fruit salad
directions: Other fresh fruit may be added.
Combine all fruits and set aside.
Mix well; 2 tablespoons sugar, orange juice, lime juice and melon liqueur.
Pour over the fruit and chill one hour. Serves 6.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash and drain okra; cut into pieces (not too thin) into large bowl.
Sprinkle with the cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Heat large saucepan; add shortening on medium.
When melted, raise heat to medium-high and pour in okra.
Wait for 2 to 3 minutes.
Lower heat back to medium.
Now in about 5 to 8 minutes, take spatula and lift and turn okra.
Do not stir this okra up, please lift and turn to make a crispy fried okra.
Lower the heat a little so as not to burn, please.
May add more cornmeal.
Make sure okra is well coated with the meal.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Stuff in pita bread.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Wrap each breast in bacon.
Cover bottom of 8 x 12-inch dish with chipped beef. Place chicken in casserole.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Pour over breasts and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth.
Yields 2 cups.

title: peanut ice cream
directions: Combine eggs and brown sugar; set aside.
Heat milk in a large saucepan over medium heat until hot.
Gradually stir a small amount of hot milk into egg mixture; add to remaining hot milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until thermometer reaches 160° (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and cool.
Stir in whipping cream and peanuts.
Pour mixture into freezer container of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer. Freeze mixture according to manufacturer's instructions.
Pack freezer with additional ice and rock salt; let stand 1 hour.
Serve with hot fudge sauce. Garnish, if desired.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Using a heavy cleaver or meat mallet, flatten each breast half to about a 1/4-inch thickness.
Place one slice of ham and one slice of cheese on each breast.
Beginning at narrow end, roll up and press meat firmly together.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: aunt ida's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill 1 hour or more.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Do not get too brown.

title: pineapple cheese dessert(diabetic)
directions: Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs, reserving 3 tablespoons for topping.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press evenly in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Combine cottage cheese, lemon juice, lemon rind, salt, pineapple and artificial sweetener in blender container; process until smooth.
Add to gelatin; blend well.
Chill until mixture is partially set.
Pour into crust; chill until firm.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Garnish with thin peels of lemon.
Yields 8 servings.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Combine with remaining ingredients and chill before serving.

title: carp chowder
directions: Poach carp in water with onion, tarragon and sliced lemon with peel left on until fish is nearly done.
Remove from heat and pick flesh from bones.

title: chocolate chip pecan cake
directions: Combine all ingredients for cake until well blended. Bake at 325° in preheated oven in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and allow to cool completely before icing.

title: hawaiian cream dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine pineapple and 1/4 cup liquid, marshmallows and cherries.
Let stand 1 hour. Fold in whipped cream.
Put in individual serving dishes.
Chill; sprinkle with almonds and coconut.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy pasta salad with vegetables
directions: Cook pasta, pour on Caesar salad while still warm.
Thaw vegetables and add.
Cut up black olives and add with salad seasoning.

title: chicken ala hap
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate mixture 1 hour, stirring chicken after 1/2 hour.
Grill on aluminum foil on low heat (about 1 hour) or bake covered with foil at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover to brown.

title: barbecued round steak
directions: Cut meat into 6 serving pieces.
In large skillet or Dutch oven, brown meat in oil over medium heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly; cook on top of range or in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: white fudge candy
directions: Bring sugar, skimmed milk and butter to soft ball boil stage, then add peanut butter and marshmallows.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Pare apples and dice. Set aside with sugar over them in a bowl.
Mix flour, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Add nuts if desired.
Add apple mixture. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Yum!
Yum!
Fattening!

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make a layer in bottom of pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Pour over layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: foolproof fudge(serves 30.  preparation :05.  cook :15.  total :20.)
directions: Place margarine, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts in large bowl. Set aside. In large 5-quart heavy saucepan, bring sugar and milk to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil and continue stirring for 8 minutes (mixture will bubble up). Pour milk mixture over chocolate mixture and stir to blend. Beat with electric mixer approximately 2 minutes until smooth and creamy. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy cucumber pickles
directions: Fill gallon jug with cucumbers standing end to end (7 to 8 pounds).
Add salt; cover with cider vinegar.
Tie cloth over jug; let stand 6 weeks.
Do nothing.
At end of 6 weeks, drain off vinegar.
Rinse well.
Dry with paper towels.
Slice cucumbers thin; put back in jug.
Add 2 to 3 drops oil of cloves.
Layer cucumbers with sugar.
Wait 2 weeks.
Serve.
Do not have to refrigerate, always crisp.

title: loraine's potato casserole
directions: In the largest bowl you can find, stir together the soups, sour cream, 1/2 stick (1/4 cup) melted butter or margarine, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add the grated cheese.
Stir until evenly distributed.
Stir in the frozen hash brown potatoes. Spoon mixture into a 10 x 15-inch baking dish (or into two 8 x 8-inch dishes), and level with back of spoon.
Cover with crushed cornflakes.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter.
Drizzle over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow to stand for 20 minutes before serving.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Bring Karo syrup to a boil, then add sugar and peanut butter. Stir until creamy. Remove from heat and add corn flakes. Stir and put in buttered pan.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper and onion.
Put in large bowl and cover with sugar.
Heat vinegar, oil, salt, mustard and celery seed to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Pack in jars and chill.
Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Sprinkle with salt. Spread on paper towels; let stand 20 minutes to dry.
Dip each slice into mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil.
Brown eggplant quickly over medium heat.
Drain on paper towels. Continue cooking slices.
Add more oil to pan if needed to cook all slices.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk in a large bowl and refrigerate one hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in cherry pie filling first.
Stil well and refrigerate overnight.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Pinch
off
enough to make each pie. Can roll out and stack on top of each other for a number of pies. Then
you
are
through
with the dough.
Dough will keep
several days
in refrigerator.

title: almond squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 8-inch greased square pan.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Remove from oven and bang 4 to 5 times on the counter (cake will flatten).
Return to oven for 10 minutes more, until light brown around edges.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in a large bowl.
Mix vinegar, water and 1 teaspoon sugar and pour over salad.
Blend cottage cheese until creamy.
Add sugar and spices.
Blend well.
Spread mixture over salad.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook rice in 5 cups boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
Cook onions in butter until limp but not browned.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: cris' ice tea
directions: Boil 3 quarts water; add 13 tea bags (it's easier to twist strings of bags together for less of a mess) and remove from heat. Let sit approximately 1/2 hour.
Drain and squeeze tea bags and remove.
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Stir well until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into a gallon jug; add enough cold water to make 1 gallon.
Stir or shake well.
Chill and serve over ice.

title: luscious coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making 2 layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; blend well and chill.
Reserve one cup sour cream mixture for frosting and spread remainder between layers of cake.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in an airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
